{"term": "1989", "caseName": "North Dakota v. United States", "caseLink": "https://www.oyez.org/cases/1989/88-926", "caseTranscripts": [{"transcriptTitle": "Oral Argument - October 31, 1989", "transcriptLink": "https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/rehnquist3/oral_argument_audio/18189", "transcript": [{"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "We'll hear argument next in Number 88-926, North Dakota versus the United States.", "start": 0, "stop": 8.92, "duration": 8.92, "cleanText": [["we", "will", "hear", "argument", "next", "in", "number", "north", "dakota", "versus", "the", "united", "state"]]}, {"text": "General Speath, you may proceed.", "start": 8.92, "stop": 59.242, "duration": 50.32, "cleanText": [["general", "speath", "you", "may", "proceed"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you.", "start": 59.242, "stop": 60.164, "duration": 0.92, "cleanText": [["thank", "you"]]}, {"text": "Chief Justice Rehnquist, members of the Court, and may it please the Court:", "start": 60.164, "stop": 63.802, "duration": 3.64, "cleanText": [["chief", "justice", "rehnquist", "member", "of", "the", "court", "and", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "It is a special privilege for me to be here because it is only two ways shy of the State of North Dakota's hundredth birthday.", "start": 63.802, "stop": 69.706, "duration": 5.9, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "a", "special", "privilege", "for", "me", "to", "be", "here", "because", "it", "be", "only", "two", "way", "shy", "of", "the", "state", "of", "north", "dakota", "s", "hundredth", "birthday"]]}, {"text": "The question presented in this case is whether the state, in an effort to prevent bootlegging of liquor from military enclaves, may impose a requirement on the suppliers of that liquor to the bases that requires them to put a label on each bottle destined for the military enclave indicating it is to be consumed only on the base.", "start": 69.706, "stop": 88.37, "duration": 18.66, "cleanText": [["the", "question", "present", "in", "this", "case", "be", "whether", "the", "state", "in", "an", "effort", "to", "prevent", "bootlegging", "of", "liquor", "from", "military", "enclave", "may", "impose", "a", "requirement", "on", "the", "supplier", "of", "that", "liquor", "to", "the", "base", "that", "require", "them", "to", "put", "a", "label", "on", "each", "bottle", "destine", "for", "the", "military", "enclave", "indicate", "it", "be", "to", "be", "consume", "only", "on", "the", "base"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, that isn't all the law says, is it?", "start": 88.37, "stop": 91.963, "duration": 3.59, "cleanText": [["well", "that", "be", "not", "all", "the", "law", "say", "be", "it"]]}, {"text": "You can avoid putting that label on if you do something else.", "start": 91.963, "stop": 96.429, "duration": 4.47, "cleanText": [["you", "can", "avoid", "put", "that", "label", "on", "if", "you", "do", "something", "else"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "If you buy it from a local distributor, that is correct.", "start": 96.429, "stop": 100.632, "duration": 4.2, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "buy", "it", "from", "a", "local", "distributor", "that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh yeah, yeah.", "start": 100.632, "stop": 103.195, "duration": 2.56, "cleanText": [["oh", "yeah", "yeah"]]}, {"text": "[Laughter]", "start": 103.195, "stop": 103.818, "duration": 0.62, "cleanText": [["laughter"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct, and pay the tax.", "start": 103.818, "stop": 104.787, "duration": 0.97, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "and", "pay", "the", "tax"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "All right, all right.", "start": 104.787, "stop": 105.928, "duration": 1.14, "cleanText": [["all", "right", "all", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "We don't have a bootlegging problem with that, because there isn't a price differential.", "start": 105.928, "stop": 109.442, "duration": 3.51, "cleanText": [["we", "do", "not", "have", "a", "bootlegging", "problem", "with", "that", "because", "there", "be", "not", "a", "price", "differential"]]}, {"text": "And that is in fact--", "start": 109.442, "stop": 110.177, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "in", "fact"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, why would that... don't you want to keep the... you don't want... you can't even use the liquor off the base--", "start": 110.177, "stop": 120.047, "duration": 9.87, "cleanText": [["well", "why", "would", "that", "do", "not", "you", "want", "to", "keep", "the", "you", "do", "not", "want", "you", "can", "not", "even", "use", "the", "liquor", "off", "the", "base"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "--That is correct.", "start": 120.047, "stop": 120.781, "duration": 0.73, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--under this law.", "start": 120.781, "stop": 121.266, "duration": 0.48, "cleanText": [["under", "this", "law"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct.", "start": 121.266, "stop": 122.016, "duration": 0.75, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "But if you... if it is bought from a local distributor--", "start": 122.016, "stop": 126.387, "duration": 4.37, "cleanText": [["but", "if", "you", "if", "it", "be", "buy", "from", "a", "local", "distributor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct.", "start": 126.387, "stop": 127.653, "duration": 1.27, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--you may take it off the base.", "start": 127.653, "stop": 128.511, "duration": 0.86, "cleanText": [["you", "may", "take", "it", "off", "the", "base"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct, because the taxes have been paid.", "start": 128.511, "stop": 130.136, "duration": 1.63, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "because", "the", "tax", "have", "be", "pay"]]}, {"text": "And--", "start": 130.136, "stop": 132.322, "duration": 2.19, "cleanText": [["and"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, what's the purpose of the North Dakota requirement?", "start": 132.322, "stop": 135.712, "duration": 3.39, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "be", "the", "purpose", "of", "the", "north", "dakota", "requirement"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "--To prevent bootlegging of the liquor off the base.", "start": 135.712, "stop": 138.664, "duration": 2.95, "cleanText": [["to", "prevent", "bootlegging", "of", "the", "liquor", "off", "the", "base"]]}, {"text": "There is a price differential between liquor sold on the base and off the base, because off-the-base liquor sales are subject to the distribution system and the state taxation.", "start": 138.664, "stop": 148.27, "duration": 9.61, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "a", "price", "differential", "between", "liquor", "sell", "on", "the", "base", "and", "off", "the", "base", "because", "off", "the", "base", "liquor", "sale", "be", "subject", "to", "the", "distribution", "system", "and", "the", "state", "taxation"]]}, {"text": "On-base sales are not.", "start": 148.27, "stop": 149.534, "duration": 1.26, "cleanText": [["on", "base", "sale", "be", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "What sorts of diversions constitute the evil or the problem?", "start": 149.534, "stop": 153.956, "duration": 4.42, "cleanText": [["what", "sort", "of", "diversion", "constitute", "the", "evil", "or", "the", "problem"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, if I can confine myself to answer your question, first of all, solely to the record.", "start": 153.956, "stop": 159.328, "duration": 5.37, "cleanText": [["well", "if", "i", "can", "confine", "myself", "to", "answer", "your", "question", "first", "of", "all", "solely", "to", "the", "record"]]}, {"text": "In North Dakota the state treasury became aware of liquor being shipped off base and used by people off the premises and being distributed to other individuals who are not authorized to have it.", "start": 159.328, "stop": 168.512, "duration": 9.18, "cleanText": [["in", "north", "dakota", "the", "state", "treasury", "become", "aware", "of", "liquor", "be", "ship", "off", "base", "and", "use", "by", "people", "off", "the", "premise", "and", "be", "distribute", "to", "other", "individual", "who", "be", "not", "authorize", "to", "have", "it"]]}, {"text": "In the State of Hawaii one enterprising person managed to get enough liquor off the base to actually supply a complete liquor store within Hawaii.", "start": 168.512, "stop": 176.055, "duration": 7.54, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "state", "of", "hawaii", "one", "enterprising", "person", "manage", "to", "get", "enough", "liquor", "off", "the", "base", "to", "actually", "supply", "a", "complete", "liquor", "store", "within", "hawaii"]]}, {"text": "In the State of Washington, enough liquor was shipped to one particular military enclave where, if it were to be consumed on base, each individual would have had to consume five bottles per day, every day of the year.", "start": 176.055, "stop": 186.832, "duration": 10.78, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "state", "of", "washington", "enough", "liquor", "be", "ship", "to", "one", "particular", "military", "enclave", "where", "if", "it", "we", "be", "to", "be", "consume", "on", "base", "each", "individual", "would", "have", "have", "to", "consume", "five", "bottle", "per", "day", "every", "day", "of", "the", "year"]]}, {"text": "And anyone who has ever been around--", "start": 186.832, "stop": 188.956, "duration": 2.12, "cleanText": [["and", "anyone", "who", "have", "ever", "be", "around"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is that supposed to tax our credibility?", "start": 188.956, "stop": 190.831, "duration": 1.88, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "suppose", "to", "tax", "our", "credibility"]]}, {"text": "[Laughter]", "start": 190.831, "stop": 191.846, "duration": 1.02, "cleanText": [["laughter"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, anybody who has been around military bases knows that there is a little bit of drinking that goes on, but I think that is more than... than its share.", "start": 191.846, "stop": 200.421, "duration": 8.57, "cleanText": [["well", "anybody", "who", "have", "be", "around", "military", "base", "know", "that", "there", "be", "a", "little", "bit", "of", "drinking", "that", "go", "on", "but", "i", "think", "that", "be", "more", "than", "than", "its", "share"]]}, {"text": "And that is precisely what this regulation is designed to do.", "start": 200.421, "stop": 203.279, "duration": 2.86, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "precisely", "what", "this", "regulation", "be", "design", "to", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Does the record show that the labeling requirement is what caused the out of state suppliers to stop supplying liquor to the government?", "start": 203.279, "stop": 212.15, "duration": 8.87, "cleanText": [["do", "the", "record", "show", "that", "the", "labeling", "requirement", "be", "what", "cause", "the", "out", "of", "state", "supplier", "to", "stop", "supply", "liquor", "to", "the", "government"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, it does not.", "start": 212.15, "stop": 213.134, "duration": 0.98, "cleanText": [["no", "it", "do", "not"]]}, {"text": "There is, however, of course, a chronological link because once the labeling requirement went into effect, several suppliers indicated that they would prefer to supply through the regular distribution system.", "start": 213.134, "stop": 224.957, "duration": 11.82, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "however", "of", "course", "a", "chronological", "link", "because", "once", "the", "labeling", "requirement", "go", "into", "effect", "several", "supplier", "indicate", "that", "they", "would", "prefer", "to", "supply", "through", "the", "regular", "distribution", "system"]]}, {"text": "Others said that they would go ahead and supply it anyway, and others said we are going to supply it, but it is going to cost you more.", "start": 224.957, "stop": 230.206, "duration": 5.25, "cleanText": [["others", "say", "that", "they", "would", "go", "ahead", "and", "supply", "it", "anyway", "and", "others", "say", "we", "be", "go", "to", "supply", "it", "but", "it", "be", "go", "to", "cost", "you", "more"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you think you could require the federal government to affix the labels?", "start": 230.206, "stop": 234.922, "duration": 4.72, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "think", "you", "could", "require", "the", "federal", "government", "to", "affix", "the", "label"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That would be certainly more problematical then, because that would be an effort to directly regulate within the military enclave, and prior cases of this Court have not allowed states that kind of discretion.", "start": 234.922, "stop": 245.841, "duration": 10.92, "cleanText": [["that", "would", "be", "certainly", "more", "problematical", "then", "because", "that", "would", "be", "an", "effort", "to", "directly", "regulate", "within", "the", "military", "enclave", "and", "prior", "case", "of", "this", "court", "have", "not", "allow", "state", "that", "kind", "of", "discretion"]]}, {"text": "Although this is a special case in the sense that the Twenty-first Amendment interacts in this particular situation.", "start": 245.841, "stop": 251.948, "duration": 6.11, "cleanText": [["although", "this", "be", "a", "special", "case", "in", "the", "sense", "that", "the", "twenty", "first", "amendment", "interacts", "in", "this", "particular", "situation"]]}, {"text": "So although the Court hasn't tread on that ground before, it would be a, certainly a more difficult case for me were I to argue that.", "start": 251.948, "stop": 257.822, "duration": 5.87, "cleanText": [["so", "although", "the", "court", "have", "not", "tread", "on", "that", "ground", "before", "it", "would", "be", "a", "certainly", "a", "more", "difficult", "case", "for", "me", "we", "be", "i", "to", "argue", "that"]]}, {"text": "I brought some labels with me so that the Court could see what they are.", "start": 257.822, "stop": 260.601, "duration": 2.78, "cleanText": [["i", "bring", "some", "label", "with", "me", "so", "that", "the", "court", "could", "see", "what", "they", "be"]]}, {"text": "These are 16 labels.", "start": 260.601, "stop": 262.007, "duration": 1.41, "cleanText": [["these", "be", "label"]]}, {"text": "They are crack-and-peel kind of labels, like bumper stickers.", "start": 262.007, "stop": 266.1, "duration": 4.09, "cleanText": [["they", "be", "crack", "and", "peel", "kind", "of", "label", "like", "bumper", "sticker"]]}, {"text": "Peel them off and then you affix them to the bottle like that.", "start": 266.1, "stop": 269.675, "duration": 3.57, "cleanText": [["peel", "them", "off", "and", "then", "you", "affix", "them", "to", "the", "bottle", "like", "that"]]}, {"text": "They cost about three cents or five cents, in that range, to produce.", "start": 269.675, "stop": 274.142, "duration": 4.47, "cleanText": [["they", "cost", "about", "three", "cent", "or", "five", "cent", "in", "that", "range", "to", "produce"]]}, {"text": "The state generates no revenue from them--", "start": 274.142, "stop": 277.61, "duration": 3.47, "cleanText": [["the", "state", "generate", "no", "revenue", "from", "them"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Can they be... may I just ask, you're worrying about the... having somebody... an officer buy so much liquor he could open his own liquor store, he could peel off these labels pretty easily, couldn't he?", "start": 277.61, "stop": 285.122, "duration": 7.51, "cleanText": [["can", "they", "be", "may", "i", "just", "ask", "you", "be", "worry", "about", "the", "have", "somebody", "an", "officer", "buy", "so", "much", "liquor", "he", "could", "open", "his", "own", "liquor", "store", "he", "could", "peel", "off", "these", "label", "pretty", "easily", "could", "not", "he"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No, you can't.", "start": 285.122, "stop": 285.794, "duration": 0.67, "cleanText": [["no", "you", "can", "not"]]}, {"text": "I don't know--", "start": 285.794, "stop": 287.856, "duration": 2.06, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "know"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Can you peel it off the podium there?", "start": 287.856, "stop": 289.293, "duration": 1.44, "cleanText": [["can", "you", "peel", "it", "off", "the", "podium", "there"]]}, {"text": "[Laughter]", "start": 289.293, "stop": 293.962, "duration": 4.67, "cleanText": [["laughter"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "--My apologies to the Marshal.", "start": 293.962, "stop": 295.181, "duration": 1.22, "cleanText": [["my", "apology", "to", "the", "marshal"]]}, {"text": "I don't think I can.", "start": 295.181, "stop": 296.415, "duration": 1.23, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "i", "can"]]}, {"text": "[Laughter]", "start": 296.415, "stop": 298.337, "duration": 1.92, "cleanText": [["laughter"]]}, {"text": "But if there is anybody who has ever participated in a political campaign knows, as I have, the worst... the hardest thing to get people to put on, or to identify with you, is a bumper sticker, because it is very difficult to get off.", "start": 298.337, "stop": 308.331, "duration": 9.99, "cleanText": [["but", "if", "there", "be", "anybody", "who", "have", "ever", "participate", "in", "a", "political", "campaign", "know", "as", "i", "have", "the", "bad", "the", "hard", "thing", "to", "get", "people", "to", "put", "on", "or", "to", "identify", "with", "you", "be", "a", "bumper", "sticker", "because", "it", "be", "very", "difficult", "to", "get", "off"]]}, {"text": "And the same thing here.", "start": 308.331, "stop": 309.424, "duration": 1.09, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "same", "thing", "here"]]}, {"text": "You can't tear it off without leaving at least part of it on.", "start": 309.424, "stop": 311.408, "duration": 1.98, "cleanText": [["you", "can", "not", "tear", "it", "off", "without", "leave", "at", "least", "part", "of", "it", "on"]]}, {"text": "And that is why this particular kind of label was chosen for this purpose.", "start": 311.408, "stop": 314.954, "duration": 3.55, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "why", "this", "particular", "kind", "of", "label", "be", "choose", "for", "this", "purpose"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you take the position that it is not a burdensome requirement?", "start": 314.954, "stop": 317.937, "duration": 2.98, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "take", "the", "position", "that", "it", "be", "not", "a", "burdensome", "requirement"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 317.937, "stop": 320.249, "duration": 2.31, "cleanText": [["no"]]}, {"text": "Excuse me, yes, I do take the position it is not a burdensome requirement.", "start": 320.249, "stop": 324.325, "duration": 4.08, "cleanText": [["excuse", "me", "yes", "i", "do", "take", "the", "position", "it", "be", "not", "a", "burdensome", "requirement"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, then why couldn't the state just require all of the liquor sold in its stores to have the sticker that it was sold in the stores?", "start": 324.325, "stop": 330.448, "duration": 6.12, "cleanText": [["well", "then", "why", "could", "not", "the", "state", "just", "require", "all", "of", "the", "liquor", "sell", "in", "its", "store", "to", "have", "the", "sticker", "that", "it", "be", "sell", "in", "the", "store"]]}, {"text": "And then the federal government would not be impeded and you could accomplish your goal.", "start": 330.448, "stop": 335.664, "duration": 5.22, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "the", "federal", "government", "would", "not", "be", "impede", "and", "you", "could", "accomplish", "your", "goal"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, that wouldn't help us with respect to identifying liquor that is sold on the base versus liquor that might be brought in from Minnesota.", "start": 335.664, "stop": 341.882, "duration": 6.22, "cleanText": [["well", "that", "would", "not", "help", "us", "with", "respect", "to", "identify", "liquor", "that", "be", "sell", "on", "the", "base", "versus", "liquor", "that", "might", "be", "bring", "in", "from", "minnesota"]]}, {"text": "In other words, it is possible, in a border state like North Dakota, that liquor could wind up in the state that was purchased in Minnesota.", "start": 341.882, "stop": 347.8, "duration": 5.92, "cleanText": [["in", "other", "word", "it", "be", "possible", "in", "a", "border", "state", "like", "north", "dakota", "that", "liquor", "could", "wind", "up", "in", "the", "state", "that", "be", "purchase", "in", "minnesota"]]}, {"text": "And while the position you... offer just has some merit, it wouldn't enable us to distinguish liquor brought in from Minnesota or Montana or South Dakota from liquor that was brought off the bases, where tax was not collected.", "start": 347.8, "stop": 360.997, "duration": 13.2, "cleanText": [["and", "while", "the", "position", "you", "offer", "just", "have", "some", "merit", "it", "would", "not", "enable", "us", "to", "distinguish", "liquor", "bring", "in", "from", "minnesota", "or", "montana", "or", "south", "dakota", "from", "liquor", "that", "be", "bring", "off", "the", "base", "where", "tax", "be", "not", "collect"]]}, {"text": "So, I don't think approaching it the reverse way would help us.", "start": 360.997, "stop": 364.606, "duration": 3.61, "cleanText": [["so", "i", "do", "not", "think", "approach", "it", "the", "reverse", "way", "would", "help", "us"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Does the state have any regulatory interest in liquor brought in from Minnesota?", "start": 364.606, "stop": 367.932, "duration": 3.33, "cleanText": [["do", "the", "state", "have", "any", "regulatory", "interest", "in", "liquor", "bring", "in", "from", "minnesota"]]}, {"text": "Doesn't it have the same regulatory interest, or is the tax... or is that not a problem because the price is high?", "start": 367.932, "stop": 373.399, "duration": 5.47, "cleanText": [["do", "not", "it", "have", "the", "same", "regulatory", "interest", "or", "be", "the", "tax", "or", "be", "that", "not", "a", "problem", "because", "the", "price", "be", "high"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "It is not a problem because the prices are roughly equivalent, because again they go through their regular state distribution system and taxes are collected on that liquor.", "start": 373.399, "stop": 380.412, "duration": 7.01, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "a", "problem", "because", "the", "price", "be", "roughly", "equivalent", "because", "again", "they", "go", "through", "their", "regular", "state", "distribution", "system", "and", "tax", "be", "collect", "on", "that", "liquor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, what you are saying is you don't need the stickers because the market takes the place of it there.", "start": 380.412, "stop": 384.364, "duration": 3.95, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "you", "be", "say", "be", "you", "do", "not", "need", "the", "sticker", "because", "the", "market", "take", "the", "place", "of", "it", "there"]]}, {"text": "I don't understand... now I don't understand your answer to the hypothetical.", "start": 384.364, "stop": 387.238, "duration": 2.87, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "understand", "now", "i", "do", "not", "understand", "your", "answer", "to", "the", "hypothetical"]]}, {"text": "If you... if you required labels on all liquor that was sold through your own distributors, that would take care of all the problem, because it is too expensive to bring it in from Minnesota.", "start": 387.238, "stop": 396.156, "duration": 8.92, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "if", "you", "require", "label", "on", "all", "liquor", "that", "be", "sell", "through", "your", "own", "distributor", "that", "would", "take", "care", "of", "all", "the", "problem", "because", "it", "be", "too", "expensive", "to", "bring", "it", "in", "from", "minnesota"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "I am sorry, Justice Stevens.", "start": 396.156, "stop": 399.64, "duration": 3.48, "cleanText": [["i", "be", "sorry", "justice", "stevens"]]}, {"text": "I don't quite understand your question, but I'll try to answer it.", "start": 399.64, "stop": 402.778, "duration": 3.14, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "quite", "understand", "your", "question", "but", "I", "will", "try", "to", "answer", "it"]]}, {"text": "There is a substantial price difference between liquor sold on the bases in North Dakota--", "start": 402.778, "stop": 408.495, "duration": 5.72, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "a", "substantial", "price", "difference", "between", "liquor", "sell", "on", "the", "base", "in", "north", "dakota"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "I understand.", "start": 408.495, "stop": 408.932, "duration": 0.44, "cleanText": [["i", "understand"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "--and liquor sold in North Dakota, in Minnesota, in Montana and in South Dakota.", "start": 408.932, "stop": 413.43, "duration": 4.5, "cleanText": [["and", "liquor", "sell", "in", "north", "dakota", "in", "minnesota", "in", "montana", "and", "in", "south", "dakota"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "I understand, but there is no similar price differential between the Minnesota liquor and the North Dakota liquor.", "start": 413.43, "stop": 417.054, "duration": 3.62, "cleanText": [["i", "understand", "but", "there", "be", "no", "similar", "price", "differential", "between", "the", "minnesota", "liquor", "and", "the", "north", "dakota", "liquor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct.", "start": 417.054, "stop": 417.772, "duration": 0.72, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "And therefore, if you required all North Dakota wholesalers and retailers to spend the three cents for these stickers on their liquor, anything that didn't have it would either be from Minnesota or from the base.", "start": 417.772, "stop": 429.377, "duration": 11.61, "cleanText": [["and", "therefore", "if", "you", "require", "all", "north", "dakota", "wholesaler", "and", "retailer", "to", "spend", "the", "three", "cent", "for", "these", "sticker", "on", "their", "liquor", "anything", "that", "do", "not", "have", "it", "would", "either", "be", "from", "minnesota", "or", "from", "the", "base"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is right.", "start": 429.377, "stop": 429.909, "duration": 0.53, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "And presumably, it wouldn't be from Minnesota because it doesn't save any money to get it from Minnesota.", "start": 429.909, "stop": 433.625, "duration": 3.72, "cleanText": [["and", "presumably", "it", "would", "not", "be", "from", "minnesota", "because", "it", "do", "not", "save", "any", "money", "to", "get", "it", "from", "minnesota"]]}, {"text": "So you would then identify the base liquor because it wouldn't have a sticker on it.", "start": 433.625, "stop": 437.124, "duration": 3.5, "cleanText": [["so", "you", "would", "then", "identify", "the", "base", "liquor", "because", "it", "would", "not", "have", "a", "sticker", "on", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "The difficulty we have, though, is one of the two military enclaves we are talking about here is located in Grand Forks, North Dakota, and I am not... I don't know your familiarity with North Dakota geography, but that sits squarely on the border with Minnesota.", "start": 437.124, "stop": 447.714, "duration": 10.59, "cleanText": [["the", "difficulty", "we", "have", "though", "be", "one", "of", "the", "two", "military", "enclave", "we", "be", "talk", "about", "here", "be", "locate", "in", "grand", "fork", "north", "dakota", "and", "i", "be", "not", "i", "do", "not", "know", "your", "familiarity", "with", "north", "dakota", "geography", "but", "that", "sit", "squarely", "on", "the", "border", "with", "minnesota"]]}, {"text": "And we would have liquor in North Dakota from Minnesota, and we'd have lots of it, because of sales or whatever features that may cause people to purchase across the... the border.", "start": 447.714, "stop": 457.521, "duration": 9.81, "cleanText": [["and", "we", "would", "have", "liquor", "in", "north", "dakota", "from", "minnesota", "and", "we", "would", "have", "lot", "of", "it", "because", "of", "sale", "or", "whatever", "feature", "that", "may", "because", "people", "to", "purchase", "across", "the", "the", "border"]]}, {"text": "So there still is a bootlegging problem that is dealt with by using these labels.", "start": 457.521, "stop": 461.911, "duration": 4.39, "cleanText": [["so", "there", "still", "be", "a", "bootlegging", "problem", "that", "be", "deal", "with", "by", "use", "these", "label"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm really, I don't... aren't there Minnesota tax stamps on the Minnesota liquor?", "start": 461.911, "stop": 464.972, "duration": 3.06, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "really", "i", "do", "not", "be", "not", "there", "minnesota", "tax", "stamp", "on", "the", "minnesota", "liquor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, there are not.", "start": 464.972, "stop": 466.081, "duration": 1.11, "cleanText": [["no", "there", "be", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "There are not.", "start": 466.081, "stop": 466.705, "duration": 0.62, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "Only the federal tax stamp exists on both North Dakota and Minnesota liquor.", "start": 466.705, "stop": 469.595, "duration": 2.89, "cleanText": [["only", "the", "federal", "tax", "stamp", "exist", "on", "both", "north", "dakota", "and", "minnesota", "liquor"]]}, {"text": "And so we do have an identification problem.", "start": 469.595, "stop": 472.984, "duration": 3.39, "cleanText": [["and", "so", "we", "do", "have", "an", "identification", "problem"]]}, {"text": "In any event, if you look at it simply from the standpoint of practicalities, this is probably the least intrusive thing the State of North Dakota could have done to deal with what it perceived to be a major problem.", "start": 472.984, "stop": 482.527, "duration": 9.54, "cleanText": [["in", "any", "event", "if", "you", "look", "at", "it", "simply", "from", "the", "standpoint", "of", "practicality", "this", "be", "probably", "the", "least", "intrusive", "thing", "the", "state", "of", "north", "dakota", "could", "have", "do", "to", "deal", "with", "what", "it", "perceive", "to", "be", "a", "major", "problem"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "General Spaeth, one of the affidavits submitted on behalf of the government indicated that one out-of-state wholesaler said he was going to have to raise his price something like $20 a case if this requirement went into effect.", "start": 482.527, "stop": 496.553, "duration": 14.03, "cleanText": [["general", "spaeth", "one", "of", "the", "affidavit", "submit", "on", "behalf", "of", "the", "government", "indicate", "that", "one", "out", "of", "state", "wholesaler", "say", "he", "be", "go", "to", "have", "to", "raise", "his", "price", "something", "like", "a", "case", "if", "this", "requirement", "go", "into", "effect"]]}, {"text": "Are there more costs connected with it, the putting on the label, than we might guess, or is this just a rather extravagant estimate, in your view?", "start": 496.553, "stop": 503.91, "duration": 7.36, "cleanText": [["be", "there", "more", "cost", "connect", "with", "it", "the", "put", "on", "the", "label", "than", "we", "might", "guess", "or", "be", "this", "just", "a", "rather", "extravagant", "estimate", "in", "your", "view"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think it is a rather extravagant estimate.", "start": 503.91, "stop": 507.237, "duration": 3.33, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "it", "be", "a", "rather", "extravagant", "estimate"]]}, {"text": "I mean, the labels themselves only cost a couple of pennies each.", "start": 507.237, "stop": 510.095, "duration": 2.86, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "the", "label", "themselves", "only", "cost", "a", "couple", "of", "penny", "each"]]}, {"text": "And unless their labor costs are enormous, it is hard to believe it would cost that much money to affix these labels.", "start": 510.095, "stop": 515.764, "duration": 5.67, "cleanText": [["and", "unless", "their", "labor", "cost", "be", "enormous", "it", "be", "hard", "to", "believe", "it", "would", "cost", "that", "much", "money", "to", "affix", "these", "label"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Let me ask you one more question.", "start": 515.764, "stop": 517.654, "duration": 1.89, "cleanText": [["let", "me", "ask", "you", "one", "more", "question"]]}, {"text": "The posture of the case is that the district court granted summary judgment for the state; the Eighth Circuit reversed and granted summary judgment for the United States.", "start": 517.654, "stop": 527.572, "duration": 9.92, "cleanText": [["the", "posture", "of", "the", "case", "be", "that", "the", "district", "court", "grant", "summary", "judgment", "for", "the", "state", "the", "eighth", "circuit", "reverse", "and", "grant", "summary", "judgment", "for", "the", "united", "state"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct.", "start": 527.572, "stop": 528.571, "duration": 1, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "So if there were any triable issue in fact in the case, both courts were wrong, in effect.", "start": 528.571, "stop": 532.381, "duration": 3.81, "cleanText": [["so", "if", "there", "we", "be", "any", "triable", "issue", "in", "fact", "in", "the", "case", "both", "court", "we", "be", "wrong", "in", "effect"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is right, although both sides stipulated to most of the essential facts in this case.", "start": 532.381, "stop": 537.083, "duration": 4.7, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right", "although", "both", "side", "stipulate", "to", "most", "of", "the", "essential", "fact", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "So it... it's really not a case where there is a real quibble over the factual record.", "start": 537.083, "stop": 542.222, "duration": 5.14, "cleanText": [["so", "it", "it", "be", "really", "not", "a", "case", "where", "there", "be", "a", "real", "quibble", "over", "the", "factual", "record"]]}, {"text": "It is rather the inferences to be drawn from the factual record.", "start": 542.222, "stop": 545.252, "duration": 3.03, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "rather", "the", "inference", "to", "be", "draw", "from", "the", "factual", "record"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I think there is a disagreement among you as to whether there is a \"burden\" or not.", "start": 545.252, "stop": 549.875, "duration": 4.62, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think", "there", "be", "a", "disagreement", "among", "you", "as", "to", "whether", "there", "be", "a", "burden", "or", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct.", "start": 549.875, "stop": 550.641, "duration": 0.77, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "And I am not so sure that isn't a factual question.", "start": 550.641, "stop": 552.592, "duration": 1.95, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "be", "not", "so", "sure", "that", "be", "not", "a", "factual", "question"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "And, it could be, in some sense of the word, because obviously the federal government is arguing that it is extremely burdensome to comply with this requirement, and the state is arguing to the contrary.", "start": 552.592, "stop": 561.464, "duration": 8.87, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "could", "be", "in", "some", "sense", "of", "the", "word", "because", "obviously", "the", "federal", "government", "be", "argue", "that", "it", "be", "extremely", "burdensome", "to", "comply", "with", "this", "requirement", "and", "the", "state", "be", "argue", "to", "the", "contrary"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "I... I take it the $20 a case figure could include also the substantial cost of having to keep separate inventories in the warehouse of the stickered and the non-stickered liquor.", "start": 561.464, "stop": 574.444, "duration": 12.98, "cleanText": [["i", "i", "take", "it", "the", "a", "case", "figure", "could", "include", "also", "the", "substantial", "cost", "of", "have", "to", "keep", "separate", "inventory", "in", "the", "warehouse", "of", "the", "stickered", "and", "the", "non", "stickered", "liquor"]]}, {"text": "Because the stickers are put on, I assume, before it is put in the box and well before it is shipped.", "start": 574.444, "stop": 579.863, "duration": 5.42, "cleanText": [["because", "the", "sticker", "be", "put", "on", "i", "assume", "before", "it", "be", "put", "in", "the", "box", "and", "well", "before", "it", "be", "ship"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 579.863, "stop": 580.769, "duration": 0.91, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "It could account for some of that cost to go, again--", "start": 580.769, "stop": 583.722, "duration": 2.95, "cleanText": [["it", "could", "account", "for", "some", "of", "that", "cost", "to", "go", "again"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "And of course, if your view prevails, you can have every state requiring stickers and then the distiller would have to keep 49 separate inventories.", "start": 583.722, "stop": 591.015, "duration": 7.29, "cleanText": [["and", "of", "course", "if", "your", "view", "prevail", "you", "can", "have", "every", "state", "require", "sticker", "and", "then", "the", "distiller", "would", "have", "to", "keep", "separate", "inventory"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Unless the states got together and agreed on a sample labeling procedure, that is correct.", "start": 591.015, "stop": 595.95, "duration": 4.94, "cleanText": [["unless", "the", "state", "get", "together", "and", "agree", "on", "a", "sample", "labeling", "procedure", "that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "The state doesn't attempt, of course, to regulate sales on the base in any other way.", "start": 595.95, "stop": 602.885, "duration": 6.93, "cleanText": [["the", "state", "do", "not", "attempt", "of", "course", "to", "regulate", "sale", "on", "the", "base", "in", "any", "other", "way"]]}, {"text": "None of this liquor is taxed.", "start": 602.885, "stop": 604.213, "duration": 1.33, "cleanText": [["none", "of", "this", "liquor", "be", "tax"]]}, {"text": "The bases operate at different hours than liquor stores within the state, and sell to any classes, individuals, it wants to on the base, and at different ages.", "start": 604.213, "stop": 613.366, "duration": 9.15, "cleanText": [["the", "base", "operate", "at", "different", "hour", "than", "liquor", "store", "within", "the", "state", "and", "sell", "to", "any", "class", "individual", "it", "want", "to", "on", "the", "base", "and", "at", "different", "age"]]}, {"text": "You can buy liquor on the Air Force bases in North Dakota when you are 18.", "start": 613.366, "stop": 616.847, "duration": 3.48, "cleanText": [["you", "can", "buy", "liquor", "on", "the", "air", "force", "base", "in", "north", "dakota", "when", "you", "be"]]}, {"text": "You have to wait until you are 21 within the state.", "start": 616.847, "stop": 618.847, "duration": 2, "cleanText": [["you", "have", "to", "wait", "until", "you", "be", "within", "the", "state"]]}, {"text": "The state believed it had the authority to impose this labeling requirement because of its inherent police powers, and also because of its core powers within the Twenty-first Amendment.", "start": 618.847, "stop": 627.672, "duration": 8.83, "cleanText": [["the", "state", "believe", "it", "have", "the", "authority", "to", "impose", "this", "labeling", "requirement", "because", "of", "its", "inherent", "police", "power", "and", "also", "because", "of", "its", "core", "power", "within", "the", "twenty", "first", "amendment"]]}, {"text": "Indeed we thought in doing this we were doing exactly what this Court suggested that we do in United States v. Mississippi Tax Commission, when the Court alluded to the fact that the states were free, of course, to regulate the shipments of liquor en route to bases in order to prevent diversion.", "start": 627.672, "stop": 644.04, "duration": 16.37, "cleanText": [["indeed", "we", "think", "in", "do", "this", "we", "we", "be", "do", "exactly", "what", "this", "court", "suggest", "that", "we", "do", "in", "united", "state", "v", "mississippi", "tax", "commission", "when", "the", "court", "allude", "to", "the", "fact", "that", "the", "state", "we", "be", "free", "of", "course", "to", "regulate", "the", "shipment", "of", "liquor", "en", "route", "to", "base", "in", "order", "to", "prevent", "diversion"]]}, {"text": "But notwithstanding what we thought to be a fairly innocuous regulation, and our belief that it was firmly rooted in prior cases of this Court, the federal government chose to challenge it.", "start": 644.04, "stop": 657.066, "duration": 13.03, "cleanText": [["but", "notwithstanding", "what", "we", "think", "to", "be", "a", "fairly", "innocuous", "regulation", "and", "our", "belief", "that", "it", "be", "firmly", "root", "in", "prior", "case", "of", "this", "court", "the", "federal", "government", "choose", "to", "challenge", "it"]]}, {"text": "And as the Court has already noted, the Eighth Circuit overturned the regulations on a two to one vote.", "start": 657.066, "stop": 661.439, "duration": 4.37, "cleanText": [["and", "as", "the", "court", "have", "already", "note", "the", "eighth", "circuit", "overturn", "the", "regulation", "on", "a", "two", "to", "one", "vote"]]}, {"text": "The court of appeals found the regulation invalid, I believe, because it mischaracterized it.", "start": 661.439, "stop": 666.907, "duration": 5.47, "cleanText": [["the", "court", "of", "appeal", "find", "the", "regulation", "invalid", "i", "believe", "because", "it", "mischaracterized", "it"]]}, {"text": "It saw the regulation as a direct effort to regulate sales of liquor on the base, and that is clearly not the case.", "start": 666.907, "stop": 673.231, "duration": 6.32, "cleanText": [["it", "saw", "the", "regulation", "as", "a", "direct", "effort", "to", "regulate", "sale", "of", "liquor", "on", "the", "base", "and", "that", "be", "clearly", "not", "the", "case"]]}, {"text": "The regulation only applies to the suppliers.", "start": 673.231, "stop": 675.683, "duration": 2.45, "cleanText": [["the", "regulation", "only", "apply", "to", "the", "supplier"]]}, {"text": "It is really like a host of other state regulations that indirectly affect federal procurement: safety regulations, minimum wage regulations, environmental regulations, even the highway speed limit.", "start": 675.683, "stop": 686.304, "duration": 10.62, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "really", "like", "a", "host", "of", "other", "state", "regulation", "that", "indirectly", "affect", "federal", "procurement", "safety", "regulation", "minimum", "wage", "regulation", "environmental", "regulation", "even", "the", "highway", "speed", "limit"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "xxx I gather, if the... if you don't comply with the labeling, then you have to be... work through the state wholesalers--", "start": 686.304, "stop": 698.331, "duration": 12.03, "cleanText": [["xxx", "i", "gather", "if", "the", "if", "you", "do", "not", "comply", "with", "the", "labeling", "then", "you", "have", "to", "be", "work", "through", "the", "state", "wholesaler"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is right.", "start": 698.331, "stop": 699.282, "duration": 0.95, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--and you have to pay the tax, and inevitably, the price of liquor then delivered to the base will go up.", "start": 699.282, "stop": 705.639, "duration": 6.36, "cleanText": [["and", "you", "have", "to", "pay", "the", "tax", "and", "inevitably", "the", "price", "of", "liquor", "then", "deliver", "to", "the", "base", "will", "go", "up"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct.", "start": 705.639, "stop": 706.28, "duration": 0.64, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Every bottle will be... will cost more.", "start": 706.28, "stop": 709.091, "duration": 2.81, "cleanText": [["every", "bottle", "will", "be", "will", "cost", "more"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is right, because the tax will be--", "start": 709.091, "stop": 710.435, "duration": 1.34, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right", "because", "the", "tax", "will", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "And in the long run the people on the base will be paying the same price as... as people pay off the base at local stores.", "start": 710.435, "stop": 717.838, "duration": 7.4, "cleanText": [["and", "in", "the", "long", "run", "the", "people", "on", "the", "base", "will", "be", "pay", "the", "same", "price", "as", "as", "people", "pay", "off", "the", "base", "at", "local", "store"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "--That assumes that they are going to go through the distribution network, and many of the stores--", "start": 717.838, "stop": 721.931, "duration": 4.09, "cleanText": [["that", "assume", "that", "they", "be", "go", "to", "go", "through", "the", "distribution", "network", "and", "many", "of", "the", "store"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I know, but if they don't label they go through that.", "start": 721.931, "stop": 723.664, "duration": 1.73, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "know", "but", "if", "they", "do", "not", "label", "they", "go", "through", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "--That is correct.", "start": 723.664, "stop": 724.367, "duration": 0.7, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "But of course, they are free to label it and the Air Force is free to buy, of course, from whomever it wants.", "start": 724.367, "stop": 729.692, "duration": 5.33, "cleanText": [["but", "of", "course", "they", "be", "free", "to", "label", "it", "and", "the", "air", "force", "be", "free", "to", "buy", "of", "course", "from", "whomever", "it", "want"]]}, {"text": "There is no requirement for the Air Force purchase through the distribution system.", "start": 729.692, "stop": 732.91, "duration": 3.22, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "requirement", "for", "the", "air", "force", "purchase", "through", "the", "distribution", "system"]]}, {"text": "And many suppliers will supply the liquor with the sticker on it, and that... the record does show that.", "start": 732.91, "stop": 738.783, "duration": 5.87, "cleanText": [["and", "many", "supplier", "will", "supply", "the", "liquor", "with", "the", "sticker", "on", "it", "and", "that", "the", "record", "do", "show", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "General Spaeth, you say it is like a lot of other state regulation.", "start": 738.783, "stop": 742.672, "duration": 3.89, "cleanText": [["general", "spaeth", "you", "say", "it", "be", "like", "a", "lot", "of", "other", "state", "regulation"]]}, {"text": "Well, in one significant respect it differs from other state regulation, and that is it explicitly applies only to sellers to the United States government.", "start": 742.672, "stop": 751.685, "duration": 9.01, "cleanText": [["well", "in", "one", "significant", "respect", "it", "differ", "from", "other", "state", "regulation", "and", "that", "be", "it", "explicitly", "apply", "only", "to", "seller", "to", "the", "united", "states", "government"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct.", "start": 751.685, "stop": 752.355, "duration": 0.67, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "But that is because--", "start": 752.355, "stop": 753.277, "duration": 0.92, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "be", "because"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is a big difference.", "start": 753.277, "stop": 753.808, "duration": 0.53, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "a", "big", "difference"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, it is a difference, but it is a discrimination in favor of the federal government, because every other distributor has to pay the tax and go through the whole distribution network, be licensed and be bonded.", "start": 753.808, "stop": 764.866, "duration": 11.06, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "be", "a", "difference", "but", "it", "be", "a", "discrimination", "in", "favor", "of", "the", "federal", "government", "because", "every", "other", "distributor", "have", "to", "pay", "the", "tax", "and", "go", "through", "the", "whole", "distribution", "network", "be", "license", "and", "be", "bond"]]}, {"text": "It is exactly like the situation this Court endorsed in United States v. Washington, where the state of Washington imposed a tax on federal contractors that was different than the tax imposed on other contractors within the state.", "start": 764.866, "stop": 778.61, "duration": 13.74, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "exactly", "like", "the", "situation", "this", "court", "endorse", "in", "united", "state", "v", "washington", "where", "the", "state", "of", "washington", "impose", "a", "tax", "on", "federal", "contractor", "that", "be", "different", "than", "the", "tax", "impose", "on", "other", "contractor", "within", "the", "state"]]}, {"text": "The tax was lower.", "start": 778.61, "stop": 779.938, "duration": 1.33, "cleanText": [["the", "tax", "be", "low"]]}, {"text": "And this Court said there was no problem with that.", "start": 779.938, "stop": 782.702, "duration": 2.76, "cleanText": [["and", "this", "court", "say", "there", "be", "no", "problem", "with", "that"]]}, {"text": "That is constitutional because you are not discriminating against the federal government.", "start": 782.702, "stop": 785.889, "duration": 3.19, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "constitutional", "because", "you", "be", "not", "discriminate", "against", "the", "federal", "government"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, how does this, how does this in favor of the government in any respect?", "start": 785.889, "stop": 790.091, "duration": 4.2, "cleanText": [["well", "how", "do", "this", "how", "do", "this", "in", "favor", "of", "the", "government", "in", "any", "respect"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "Because it doesn't require... we are not attempting to tax the distributor or the supplier or purveyor of liquor to the base.", "start": 790.091, "stop": 799.992, "duration": 9.9, "cleanText": [["because", "it", "do", "not", "require", "we", "be", "not", "attempt", "to", "tax", "the", "distributor", "or", "the", "supplier", "or", "purveyor", "of", "liquor", "to", "the", "base"]]}, {"text": "The tax isn't collected; the suppliers don't have to go through the state distribution system.", "start": 799.992, "stop": 804.648, "duration": 4.66, "cleanText": [["the", "tax", "be", "not", "collect", "the", "supplier", "do", "not", "have", "to", "go", "through", "the", "state", "distribution", "system"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "They just have to label.", "start": 804.648, "stop": 805.007, "duration": 0.36, "cleanText": [["they", "just", "have", "to", "label"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "They just have to label.", "start": 805.007, "stop": 806.568, "duration": 1.56, "cleanText": [["they", "just", "have", "to", "label"]]}, {"text": "It is far less onerous than what other distributors have to do within the state.", "start": 806.568, "stop": 810.691, "duration": 4.12, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "far", "less", "onerous", "than", "what", "other", "distributor", "have", "to", "do", "within", "the", "state"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you think you could do that, you could go the other route?", "start": 810.691, "stop": 814.705, "duration": 4.01, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "think", "you", "could", "do", "that", "you", "could", "go", "the", "other", "route"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "Go which route?", "start": 814.705, "stop": 818.859, "duration": 4.15, "cleanText": [["go", "which", "route"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Re... impose the tax, require the base to buy it from your... require the federal enclaves to buy it through the distributor system?", "start": 818.859, "stop": 828.075, "duration": 9.22, "cleanText": [["re", "impose", "the", "tax", "require", "the", "base", "to", "buy", "it", "from", "your", "require", "the", "federal", "enclave", "to", "buy", "it", "through", "the", "distributor", "system"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't think that the state could require the federal enclaves to buy it through the distribution system, but I do think the state, if it wanted to, could tax those suppliers before they sell the liquor to the base.", "start": 828.075, "stop": 839.445, "duration": 11.37, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "that", "the", "state", "could", "require", "the", "federal", "enclave", "to", "buy", "it", "through", "the", "distribution", "system", "but", "i", "do", "think", "the", "state", "if", "it", "want", "to", "could", "tax", "those", "supplier", "before", "they", "sell", "the", "liquor", "to", "the", "base"]]}, {"text": "Indeed, the court in the United States v. Mississippi said the states could do that, and in the case I just cited to you, United States v. the State of Washington, the Court said you could do that.", "start": 839.445, "stop": 848.614, "duration": 9.17, "cleanText": [["indeed", "the", "court", "in", "the", "united", "state", "v", "mississippi", "say", "the", "state", "could", "do", "that", "and", "in", "the", "case", "i", "just", "cite", "to", "you", "united", "state", "v", "the", "state", "of", "washington", "the", "court", "say", "you", "could", "do", "that"]]}, {"text": "You could tax contractors or suppliers to the federal government, as long as you don't do it in a discriminatory way.", "start": 848.614, "stop": 854.423, "duration": 5.81, "cleanText": [["you", "could", "tax", "contractor", "or", "supplier", "to", "the", "federal", "government", "as", "long", "as", "you", "do", "not", "do", "it", "in", "a", "discriminatory", "way"]]}, {"text": "We are doing far less than that here--", "start": 854.423, "stop": 856.375, "duration": 1.95, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "do", "far", "less", "than", "that", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is that true if the supplier... that's not true if the suppliers are out of state.", "start": 856.375, "stop": 859.811, "duration": 3.44, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "true", "if", "the", "supplier", "that", "be", "not", "true", "if", "the", "supplier", "be", "out", "of", "state"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, they are in state, though, for the purpose of doing business, in the sense that they are selling to locations within the state.", "start": 859.811, "stop": 869.09, "duration": 9.28, "cleanText": [["well", "they", "be", "in", "state", "though", "for", "the", "purpose", "of", "do", "business", "in", "the", "sense", "that", "they", "be", "sell", "to", "location", "within", "the", "state"]]}, {"text": "I mean, that, just as Sears and Roebuck is in the state in the sense that it sells within the state.", "start": 869.09, "stop": 872.995, "duration": 3.9, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "that", "just", "as", "sears", "and", "roebuck", "be", "in", "the", "state", "in", "the", "sense", "that", "it", "sell", "within", "the", "state"]]}, {"text": "And I don't think it is any different than situations this Court has endorsed in other cases.", "start": 872.995, "stop": 881.85, "duration": 8.86, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "do", "not", "think", "it", "be", "any", "different", "than", "situation", "this", "court", "have", "endorse", "in", "other", "case"]]}, {"text": "The court of appeals also thought in this case that there might be federal preemption.", "start": 881.85, "stop": 887.708, "duration": 5.86, "cleanText": [["the", "court", "of", "appeal", "also", "think", "in", "this", "case", "that", "there", "might", "be", "federal", "preemption"]]}, {"text": "It relied on a statute that requires the federal government to purchase liquor from the most competitive source, price and other factors considered, and a regulation that basically parroted the statute.", "start": 887.708, "stop": 898.202, "duration": 10.49, "cleanText": [["it", "rely", "on", "a", "statute", "that", "require", "the", "federal", "government", "to", "purchase", "liquor", "from", "the", "most", "competitive", "source", "price", "and", "other", "factor", "consider", "and", "a", "regulation", "that", "basically", "parrot", "the", "statute"]]}, {"text": "It is difficult for me to see how that could be preemption.", "start": 898.202, "stop": 902.154, "duration": 3.95, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "difficult", "for", "me", "to", "see", "how", "that", "could", "be", "preemption"]]}, {"text": "First of all, there is no express statement in either the statute or regulation that any state rules or regulations are preempted.", "start": 902.154, "stop": 908.214, "duration": 6.06, "cleanText": [["first", "of", "all", "there", "be", "no", "express", "statement", "in", "either", "the", "statute", "or", "regulation", "that", "any", "state", "rule", "or", "regulation", "be", "preempt"]]}, {"text": "Certainly this is not an area where Congress has occupied the field, indeed the Twenty-first Amendment would arguably prevent that.", "start": 908.214, "stop": 914.024, "duration": 5.81, "cleanText": [["certainly", "this", "be", "not", "an", "area", "where", "congress", "have", "occupy", "the", "field", "indeed", "the", "twenty", "first", "amendment", "would", "arguably", "prevent", "that"]]}, {"text": "And third, there is no frustration of the federal purchasing objection here.", "start": 914.024, "stop": 917.149, "duration": 3.13, "cleanText": [["and", "third", "there", "be", "no", "frustration", "of", "the", "federal", "purchasing", "objection", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, one gets the impression, General Spaeth, from reading about what Congress did, that the intent was to require the bases to purchase locally when they are talking about beer and wine, but to allow liquor to come in from out of state as well as locally, and be competitive, when you are talking about hard liquor.", "start": 917.149, "stop": 935.874, "duration": 18.73, "cleanText": [["well", "one", "get", "the", "impression", "general", "spaeth", "from", "read", "about", "what", "congress", "do", "that", "the", "intent", "be", "to", "require", "the", "base", "to", "purchase", "locally", "when", "they", "be", "talk", "about", "beer", "and", "wine", "but", "to", "allow", "liquor", "to", "come", "in", "from", "out", "of", "state", "as", "well", "as", "locally", "and", "be", "competitive", "when", "you", "be", "talk", "about", "hard", "liquor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct.", "start": 935.874, "stop": 936.593, "duration": 0.72, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "That is precisely what Congress intended.", "start": 936.593, "stop": 938.905, "duration": 2.31, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "precisely", "what", "congress", "intend"]]}, {"text": "And, obviously, it is our position, what the State of North Dakota does here doesn't interfere in any way with what Congress intended, because--", "start": 938.905, "stop": 947.808, "duration": 8.9, "cleanText": [["and", "obviously", "it", "be", "our", "position", "what", "the", "state", "of", "north", "dakota", "do", "here", "do", "not", "interfere", "in", "any", "way", "with", "what", "congress", "intend", "because"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "xxx liquor at the lowest prices available.", "start": 947.808, "stop": 951.307, "duration": 3.5, "cleanText": [["xxx", "liquor", "at", "the", "low", "price", "available"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "--That is right.", "start": 951.307, "stop": 951.822, "duration": 0.51, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "No matter what the price is, it is the lowest price that is available.", "start": 951.822, "stop": 954.462, "duration": 2.64, "cleanText": [["no", "matter", "what", "the", "price", "be", "it", "be", "the", "low", "price", "that", "be", "available"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is right, and they are free... the bases are free to buy from whatever source they want.", "start": 954.462, "stop": 958.695, "duration": 4.23, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right", "and", "they", "be", "free", "the", "base", "be", "free", "to", "buy", "from", "whatever", "source", "they", "want"]]}, {"text": "And the only thing that North Dakota requires is this little label to be affixed to those bottles.", "start": 958.695, "stop": 962.77, "duration": 4.07, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "only", "thing", "that", "north", "dakota", "require", "be", "this", "little", "label", "to", "be", "affix", "to", "those", "bottle"]]}, {"text": "So again, it is difficult to see where the preemption comes here, given the language of the statute and the regulation, and I doubt very much if that is what Congress intended to do when it enacted this particular legislation.", "start": 962.77, "stop": 973.657, "duration": 10.89, "cleanText": [["so", "again", "it", "be", "difficult", "to", "see", "where", "the", "preemption", "come", "here", "give", "the", "language", "of", "the", "statute", "and", "the", "regulation", "and", "i", "doubt", "very", "much", "if", "that", "be", "what", "congress", "intend", "to", "do", "when", "it", "enact", "this", "particular", "legislation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Harry A. Blackmun", "textObjs": [{"text": "General Spaeth, do you have any comment on the milk case of Paul against United States, and how it bears on this?", "start": 973.657, "stop": 980.56, "duration": 6.9, "cleanText": [["general", "spaeth", "do", "you", "have", "any", "comment", "on", "the", "milk", "case", "of", "paul", "against", "united", "state", "and", "how", "it", "bear", "on", "this"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Justice Blackmun.", "start": 980.56, "stop": 982.294, "duration": 1.73, "cleanText": [["yes", "justice", "blackmun"]]}, {"text": "I don't think it applies.", "start": 982.294, "stop": 983.684, "duration": 1.39, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "it", "apply"]]}, {"text": "In Paul we are dealing with a situation where California had a minimum price law with respect to milk.", "start": 983.684, "stop": 990.197, "duration": 6.51, "cleanText": [["in", "paul", "we", "be", "deal", "with", "a", "situation", "where", "california", "have", "a", "minimum", "price", "law", "with", "respect", "to", "milk"]]}, {"text": "And, obviously, any time you set a minimum that tends to be where the price falls, if you understand the marketing in milk.", "start": 990.197, "stop": 995.868, "duration": 5.67, "cleanText": [["and", "obviously", "any", "time", "you", "set", "a", "minimum", "that", "tend", "to", "be", "where", "the", "price", "fall", "if", "you", "understand", "the", "marketing", "in", "milk"]]}, {"text": "And that totally frustrated the federal objective of buying from the most competitive source available, because every quart of milk sold in California was priced at exactly the same price.", "start": 995.868, "stop": 1005.191, "duration": 9.32, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "totally", "frustrate", "the", "federal", "objective", "of", "buy", "from", "the", "most", "competitive", "source", "available", "because", "every", "quart", "of", "milk", "sell", "in", "california", "be", "price", "at", "exactly", "the", "same", "price"]]}, {"text": "That's not the situation here.", "start": 1005.191, "stop": 1006.801, "duration": 1.61, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "not", "the", "situation", "here"]]}, {"text": "We are not attempting to fix the price of liquor that is sold on the base.", "start": 1006.801, "stop": 1010.159, "duration": 3.36, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "not", "attempt", "to", "fix", "the", "price", "of", "liquor", "that", "be", "sell", "on", "the", "base"]]}, {"text": "All we are doing is imposing a requirement that according to the federal government raises its cost of buying.", "start": 1010.159, "stop": 1014.609, "duration": 4.45, "cleanText": [["all", "we", "be", "do", "be", "impose", "a", "requirement", "that", "accord", "to", "the", "federal", "government", "raise", "its", "cost", "of", "buying"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "To cure a danger to your own economy.", "start": 1014.609, "stop": 1020.216, "duration": 5.61, "cleanText": [["to", "cure", "a", "danger", "to", "your", "own", "economy"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is right, bootlegging of liquor within the state.", "start": 1020.216, "stop": 1023.184, "duration": 2.97, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right", "bootlegging", "of", "liquor", "within", "the", "state"]]}, {"text": "We think what we did here was probably the least intrusive thing we could have done, and the case is important in North Dakota, and in other states as you might guess from the volume of amicus support for the state.", "start": 1023.184, "stop": 1035.054, "duration": 11.87, "cleanText": [["we", "think", "what", "we", "do", "here", "be", "probably", "the", "least", "intrusive", "thing", "we", "could", "have", "do", "and", "the", "case", "be", "important", "in", "north", "dakota", "and", "in", "other", "state", "as", "you", "might", "guess", "from", "the", "volume", "of", "amicus", "support", "for", "the", "state"]]}, {"text": "We also felt we did what the Court invited us to do in prior cases dealing with this area.", "start": 1035.054, "stop": 1039.506, "duration": 4.45, "cleanText": [["we", "also", "felt", "we", "do", "what", "the", "court", "invite", "us", "to", "do", "in", "prior", "case", "deal", "with", "this", "area"]]}, {"text": "And, if the state can't do this, I am not sure what we can do to prevent bootlegging.", "start": 1039.506, "stop": 1045.332, "duration": 5.83, "cleanText": [["and", "if", "the", "state", "can", "not", "do", "this", "i", "be", "not", "sure", "what", "we", "can", "do", "to", "prevent", "bootlegging"]]}, {"text": "And it is for that reason I urge this Court to reverse the court of appeals before, below, and reinstate the regulation--", "start": 1045.332, "stop": 1052.828, "duration": 7.5, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "be", "for", "that", "reason", "i", "urge", "this", "court", "to", "reverse", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "before", "below", "and", "reinstate", "the", "regulation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Harry A. Blackmun", "textObjs": [{"text": "How much liquor are we talking about?", "start": 1052.828, "stop": 1054.203, "duration": 1.38, "cleanText": [["how", "much", "liquor", "be", "we", "talk", "about"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Being supplied to the base?", "start": 1054.203, "stop": 1056.717, "duration": 2.51, "cleanText": [["be", "supply", "to", "the", "base"]]}, {"text": "Lots.", "start": 1056.717, "stop": 1057.936, "duration": 1.22, "cleanText": [["lot"]]}, {"text": "There are very large enclaves, they have... there are very large Air Force bases.", "start": 1057.936, "stop": 1062.183, "duration": 4.25, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "very", "large", "enclave", "they", "have", "there", "be", "very", "large", "air", "force", "base"]]}, {"text": "Both have bombers and missiles, and there are something like 10,000 people on each base.", "start": 1062.183, "stop": 1067.338, "duration": 5.15, "cleanText": [["both", "have", "bomber", "and", "missile", "and", "there", "be", "something", "like", "people", "on", "each", "base"]]}, {"text": "In addition to that, of course, there are a host of other people who are eligible to buy, retirees, dependents.", "start": 1067.338, "stop": 1073.086, "duration": 5.75, "cleanText": [["in", "addition", "to", "that", "of", "course", "there", "be", "a", "host", "of", "other", "people", "who", "be", "eligible", "to", "buy", "retiree", "dependent"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Harry A. Blackmun", "textObjs": [{"text": "They drink a lot at Minot and Grand Forks to keep warm, I suppose.", "start": 1073.086, "stop": 1076.71, "duration": 3.62, "cleanText": [["they", "drink", "a", "lot", "at", "minot", "and", "grand", "fork", "to", "keep", "warm", "i", "suppose"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's right.", "start": 1076.71, "stop": 1077.132, "duration": 0.42, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right"]]}, {"text": "And they do also restore, or bestow honorary privileges on others.", "start": 1077.132, "stop": 1080.942, "duration": 3.81, "cleanText": [["and", "they", "do", "also", "restore", "or", "bestow", "honorary", "privilege", "on", "others"]]}, {"text": "I have honorary privileges at the Minot Air Force base, for example.", "start": 1080.942, "stop": 1084.176, "duration": 3.23, "cleanText": [["i", "have", "honorary", "privilege", "at", "the", "minot", "air", "force", "base", "for", "example"]]}, {"text": "I can go up there and drink, too.", "start": 1084.176, "stop": 1085.127, "duration": 0.95, "cleanText": [["i", "can", "go", "up", "there", "and", "drink", "too"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Harry A. Blackmun", "textObjs": [{"text": "You have an interest in this litigation.", "start": 1085.127, "stop": 1086.581, "duration": 1.45, "cleanText": [["you", "have", "an", "interest", "in", "this", "litigation"]]}, {"text": "[Laughter]", "start": 1086.581, "stop": 1088.017, "duration": 1.44, "cleanText": [["laughter"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "It cuts both ways.", "start": 1088.017, "stop": 1089.189, "duration": 1.17, "cleanText": [["it", "cut", "both", "way"]]}, {"text": "If I want to bootleg too--", "start": 1089.189, "stop": 1090.766, "duration": 1.58, "cleanText": [["if", "i", "want", "to", "bootleg", "too"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Harry A. Blackmun", "textObjs": [{"text": "Of course, what I am concerned about is your, you show no comfort for the Minnesota bootleggers who need all the help they can get.", "start": 1090.766, "stop": 1095.967, "duration": 5.2, "cleanText": [["of", "course", "what", "i", "be", "concern", "about", "be", "your", "you", "show", "no", "comfort", "for", "the", "minnesota", "bootlegger", "who", "need", "all", "the", "help", "they", "can", "get"]]}, {"text": "[Laughter]", "start": 1095.967, "stop": 1098.107, "duration": 2.14, "cleanText": [["laughter"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, the State of Minnesota's economy is doing so much better than ours these days that I have no sympathy whatsoever for it.", "start": 1098.107, "stop": 1103.745, "duration": 5.64, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "state", "of", "minnesota", "s", "economy", "be", "do", "so", "much", "good", "than", "ours", "these", "day", "that", "i", "have", "no", "sympathy", "whatsoever", "for", "it"]]}, {"text": "Notwithstanding the problems the Vikings have been having lately.", "start": 1103.745, "stop": 1107.119, "duration": 3.37, "cleanText": [["notwithstanding", "the", "problem", "the", "viking", "have", "be", "have", "lately"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "General Spaeth, I didn't understand the last statement you made.", "start": 1107.119, "stop": 1109.696, "duration": 2.58, "cleanText": [["general", "spaeth", "i", "do", "not", "understand", "the", "last", "statement", "you", "make"]]}, {"text": "You said if we don't let you do this you don't under... you don't know what you can do.", "start": 1109.696, "stop": 1113.288, "duration": 3.59, "cleanText": [["you", "say", "if", "we", "do", "not", "let", "you", "do", "this", "you", "do", "not", "under", "you", "do", "not", "know", "what", "you", "can", "do"]]}, {"text": "I thought you said earlier that you could... you could readily impose a sales tax on the sales at the base.", "start": 1113.288, "stop": 1120.27, "duration": 6.98, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "you", "say", "early", "that", "you", "could", "you", "could", "readily", "impose", "a", "sale", "tax", "on", "the", "sale", "at", "the", "base"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1120.27, "stop": 1120.489, "duration": 0.22, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}, {"text": "I think I misstated myself, Justice Scalia.", "start": 1120.489, "stop": 1122.411, "duration": 1.92, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "i", "misstate", "myself", "justice", "scalia"]]}, {"text": "We probably could--", "start": 1122.411, "stop": 1123.737, "duration": 1.33, "cleanText": [["we", "probably", "could"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Readily.", "start": 1123.737, "stop": 1124.69, "duration": 0.95, "cleanText": [["readily"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "--enforce some sort of tax, and that would lessen the price differential and help alleviate the bootlegging.", "start": 1124.69, "stop": 1130.36, "duration": 5.67, "cleanText": [["enforce", "some", "sort", "of", "tax", "and", "that", "would", "lessen", "the", "price", "differential", "and", "help", "alleviate", "the", "bootlegging"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "But not cure it.", "start": 1130.36, "stop": 1132.56, "duration": 2.2, "cleanText": [["but", "not", "cure", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "But perhaps not cure it because the military enjoys a tremendous purchasing advantage as well because of the volumes it buys.", "start": 1132.56, "stop": 1138.7, "duration": 6.14, "cleanText": [["but", "perhaps", "not", "cure", "it", "because", "the", "military", "enjoy", "a", "tremendous", "purchasing", "advantage", "as", "well", "because", "of", "the", "volume", "it", "buy"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, General Spaeth.", "start": 1138.7, "stop": 1142.308, "duration": 3.61, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "general", "spaeth"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you.", "start": 1142.308, "stop": 1142.917, "duration": 0.61, "cleanText": [["thank", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Lazerwitz.", "start": 1142.917, "stop": 1145.666, "duration": 2.75, "cleanText": [["mr", "lazerwitz"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice, and may it please the Court:", "start": 1145.666, "stop": 1149.774, "duration": 4.11, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "and", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "The military's procurement of alcoholic beverages has generated its share of controversy ever since the Congress, in 1802, included one gill, which is four ounces, of rum, whiskey or brandy in a soldier's daily ration.", "start": 1149.774, "stop": 1164.018, "duration": 14.24, "cleanText": [["the", "military", "s", "procurement", "of", "alcoholic", "beverage", "have", "generate", "its", "share", "of", "controversy", "ever", "since", "the", "congress", "in", "include", "one", "gill", "which", "be", "four", "ounce", "of", "rum", "whiskey", "or", "brandy", "in", "a", "soldier", "s", "daily", "ration"]]}, {"text": "Before this Court today the issue is whether the federal government, consistent with federal law, may remain free to purchase its alcoholic beverages for resale in military base clubs and package stores from the most convenient and inexpensive sources, regardless of whether those sources are located in a base's home state.", "start": 1164.018, "stop": 1182.713, "duration": 18.69, "cleanText": [["before", "this", "court", "today", "the", "issue", "be", "whether", "the", "federal", "government", "consistent", "with", "federal", "law", "may", "remain", "free", "to", "purchase", "its", "alcoholic", "beverage", "for", "resale", "in", "military", "base", "club", "and", "package", "store", "from", "the", "most", "convenient", "and", "inexpensive", "source", "regardless", "of", "whether", "those", "source", "be", "locate", "in", "a", "base", "s", "home", "state"]]}, {"text": "In our view the states regulations are constitutionally invalid for three principal reasons.", "start": 1182.713, "stop": 1188.866, "duration": 6.15, "cleanText": [["in", "our", "view", "the", "state", "regulation", "be", "constitutionally", "invalid", "for", "three", "principal", "reason"]]}, {"text": "First, Congress has made clear in Section 2488 of Title 10 that the military must remain free to buy its alcoholic beverages at the lowest available price, regardless of where the suppliers and/or distillers are located.", "start": 1188.866, "stop": 1204.252, "duration": 15.39, "cleanText": [["first", "congress", "have", "make", "clear", "in", "section", "of", "title", "that", "the", "military", "must", "remain", "free", "to", "buy", "its", "alcoholic", "beverage", "at", "the", "low", "available", "price", "regardless", "of", "where", "the", "supplier", "andor", "distiller", "be", "locate"]]}, {"text": "Here the record shows that North Dakota's regulatory efforts conflict with this federal scheme, actually thwart it, and thus violate the Supremacy Clause.", "start": 1204.252, "stop": 1213.561, "duration": 9.31, "cleanText": [["here", "the", "record", "show", "that", "north", "dakota", "s", "regulatory", "effort", "conflict", "with", "this", "federal", "scheme", "actually", "thwart", "it", "and", "thus", "violate", "the", "supremacy", "clause"]]}, {"text": "The regulations would in effect require the military to obtain its liquor for its North Dakota facilities from less competitive in-state sources, and on this record, at an increased annual cost of more than $200,000.", "start": 1213.561, "stop": 1226.632, "duration": 13.07, "cleanText": [["the", "regulation", "would", "in", "effect", "require", "the", "military", "to", "obtain", "its", "liquor", "for", "its", "north", "dakota", "facility", "from", "less", "competitive", "in", "state", "source", "and", "on", "this", "record", "at", "an", "increase", "annual", "cost", "of", "more", "than"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, now... but that is basically an issue of fact, don't you think, Mr. Lazerwitz?", "start": 1226.632, "stop": 1231.084, "duration": 4.45, "cleanText": [["well", "now", "but", "that", "be", "basically", "an", "issue", "of", "fact", "do", "not", "you", "think", "mr", "lazerwitz"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is clearly an issue of fact, and in this case there was an uncontroverted affidavit from Kim Keltz, that would be found at the Joint Appendix 25 to 28, and she... her affidavit stated that these regulations would in effect require the government to pay more money.", "start": 1231.084, "stop": 1247.016, "duration": 15.93, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "clearly", "an", "issue", "of", "fact", "and", "in", "this", "case", "there", "be", "an", "uncontroverted", "affidavit", "from", "kim", "keltz", "that", "would", "be", "find", "at", "the", "joint", "appendix", "to", "and", "she", "her", "affidavit", "state", "that", "these", "regulation", "would", "in", "effect", "require", "the", "government", "to", "pay", "more", "money"]]}, {"text": "And the reason isn't that hard to find.", "start": 1247.016, "stop": 1248.765, "duration": 1.75, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "reason", "be", "not", "that", "hard", "to", "find"]]}, {"text": "She testified that--", "start": 1248.765, "stop": 1250.311, "duration": 1.55, "cleanText": [["she", "testify", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "That these regulations would require the government to pay more money?", "start": 1250.311, "stop": 1253.763, "duration": 3.45, "cleanText": [["that", "these", "regulation", "would", "require", "the", "government", "to", "pay", "more", "money"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes.", "start": 1253.763, "stop": 1254.154, "duration": 0.39, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}, {"text": "And the reason isn't... isn't that difficult.", "start": 1254.154, "stop": 1256.339, "duration": 2.18, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "reason", "be", "not", "be", "not", "that", "difficult"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "But more money than what?", "start": 1256.339, "stop": 1257.776, "duration": 1.44, "cleanText": [["but", "more", "money", "than", "what"]]}, {"text": "But... I don't see how that is dispositive of a basic factual question.", "start": 1257.776, "stop": 1262.102, "duration": 4.33, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "do", "not", "see", "how", "that", "be", "dispositive", "of", "a", "basic", "factual", "question"]]}, {"text": "If... supposing out-of-state suppliers required to put on this sticker if, what Mr.... General Spaeth, says is true, they cost three cents, they will have to pass that along to the purchasers.", "start": 1262.102, "stop": 1277.362, "duration": 15.26, "cleanText": [["if", "suppose", "out", "of", "state", "supplier", "require", "to", "put", "on", "this", "sticker", "if", "what", "mr", "general", "spaeth", "say", "be", "true", "they", "cost", "three", "cent", "they", "will", "have", "to", "pass", "that", "along", "to", "the", "purchaser"]]}, {"text": "But I don't see, so long as the other state shippers are willing to keep shipping to these bases and simply add on the cost of this, I don't see how the government plan for, you know, competitive purchasing, is defeated.", "start": 1277.362, "stop": 1289.327, "duration": 11.96, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "do", "not", "see", "so", "long", "as", "the", "other", "state", "shipper", "be", "willing", "to", "keep", "shipping", "to", "these", "base", "and", "simply", "add", "on", "the", "cost", "of", "this", "i", "do", "not", "see", "how", "the", "government", "plan", "for", "you", "know", "competitive", "purchasing", "be", "defeat"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, Ms. Keltz's affidavit, she testified or explained that five of our prime source suppliers said, in light of these regulations, we are no longer going to sell directly to you.", "start": 1289.327, "stop": 1300.15, "duration": 10.82, "cleanText": [["well", "ms", "keltz", "s", "affidavit", "she", "testify", "or", "explain", "that", "five", "of", "our", "prime", "source", "supplier", "say", "in", "light", "of", "these", "regulation", "we", "be", "no", "longer", "go", "to", "sell", "directly", "to", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Okay, but do we know how many source suppliers you had?", "start": 1300.15, "stop": 1303.039, "duration": 2.89, "cleanText": [["okay", "but", "do", "we", "know", "how", "many", "source", "supplier", "you", "have"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, we don't.", "start": 1303.039, "stop": 1304.148, "duration": 1.11, "cleanText": [["no", "we", "do", "not"]]}, {"text": "The record doesn't say that.", "start": 1304.148, "stop": 1305.241, "duration": 1.09, "cleanText": [["the", "record", "do", "not", "say", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "So that proves five wouldn't do it.", "start": 1305.241, "stop": 1307.068, "duration": 1.83, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "prove", "five", "would", "not", "do", "it"]]}, {"text": "If there were 20 suppliers, maybe five not doing it would make no difference.", "start": 1307.068, "stop": 1310.677, "duration": 3.61, "cleanText": [["if", "there", "we", "be", "supplier", "maybe", "five", "not", "do", "it", "would", "make", "no", "difference"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice, the Court, in the liquor business, with both liquor that is manufactured, distilled, in this country and out of the country, there are exclusive distributors.", "start": 1310.677, "stop": 1321.141, "duration": 10.46, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "the", "court", "in", "the", "liquor", "business", "with", "both", "liquor", "that", "be", "manufacture", "distil", "in", "this", "country", "and", "out", "of", "the", "country", "there", "be", "exclusive", "distributor"]]}, {"text": "You can only buy, for example--", "start": 1321.141, "stop": 1323.22, "duration": 2.08, "cleanText": [["you", "can", "only", "buy", "for", "example"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "But is this all in the record?", "start": 1323.22, "stop": 1324.999, "duration": 1.78, "cleanText": [["but", "be", "this", "all", "in", "the", "record"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The only record support, or the record that bears on this aspect, is in the Kim Keltz affidavit, and that is not contradicted.", "start": 1324.999, "stop": 1334.293, "duration": 9.29, "cleanText": [["the", "only", "record", "support", "or", "the", "record", "that", "bear", "on", "this", "aspect", "be", "in", "the", "kim", "keltz", "affidavit", "and", "that", "be", "not", "contradict"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "And you... but, you're defending a summary judgment on the basis of a statement that five out-of-state suppliers said they would no longer supply.", "start": 1334.293, "stop": 1343.617, "duration": 9.32, "cleanText": [["and", "you", "but", "you", "be", "defend", "a", "summary", "judgment", "on", "the", "basis", "of", "a", "statement", "that", "five", "out", "of", "state", "supplier", "say", "they", "would", "no", "longer", "supply"]]}, {"text": "The record doesn't say how many potential out-of-state suppliers there were.", "start": 1343.617, "stop": 1347.724, "duration": 4.11, "cleanText": [["the", "record", "do", "not", "say", "how", "many", "potential", "out", "of", "state", "supplier", "there", "we", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "The affidavit further states... no, it doesn't, that is clear.", "start": 1347.724, "stop": 1352.207, "duration": 4.48, "cleanText": [["the", "affidavit", "further", "state", "no", "it", "do", "not", "that", "be", "clear"]]}, {"text": "But the affidavit further states that because of these prime source suppliers would no longer sell us liquor, we would have to buy those supplies from the in-state sources, the distributors.", "start": 1352.207, "stop": 1362.812, "duration": 10.6, "cleanText": [["but", "the", "affidavit", "further", "state", "that", "because", "of", "these", "prime", "source", "supplier", "would", "no", "longer", "sell", "us", "liquor", "we", "would", "have", "to", "buy", "those", "supply", "from", "the", "in", "state", "source", "the", "distributor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Suppose that all suppliers would go ahead and put the labels on with the inevitable result that the price would go up.", "start": 1362.812, "stop": 1371.2, "duration": 8.39, "cleanText": [["suppose", "that", "all", "supplier", "would", "go", "ahead", "and", "put", "the", "label", "on", "with", "the", "inevitable", "result", "that", "the", "price", "would", "go", "up"]]}, {"text": "If that were the case, there would be no interference with getting the lowest competitive price.", "start": 1371.2, "stop": 1377.338, "duration": 6.14, "cleanText": [["if", "that", "we", "be", "the", "case", "there", "would", "be", "no", "interference", "with", "get", "the", "low", "competitive", "price"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "In that respect, if in fact every state in the country had one of these... had a labeling requirement, yes.", "start": 1377.338, "stop": 1382.883, "duration": 5.55, "cleanText": [["in", "that", "respect", "if", "in", "fact", "every", "state", "in", "the", "country", "have", "one", "of", "these", "have", "a", "labeling", "requirement", "yes"]]}, {"text": "We would have a much different case.", "start": 1382.883, "stop": 1384.225, "duration": 1.34, "cleanText": [["we", "would", "have", "a", "much", "different", "case"]]}, {"text": "But there is a second aspect to this case.", "start": 1384.225, "stop": 1386.755, "duration": 2.53, "cleanText": [["but", "there", "be", "a", "second", "aspect", "to", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "But somebody has to be, some suppliers have to say no, and the base would want to... nevertheless, to purchase from those suppliers.", "start": 1386.755, "stop": 1398, "duration": 11.24, "cleanText": [["but", "somebody", "have", "to", "be", "some", "supplier", "have", "to", "say", "no", "and", "the", "base", "would", "want", "to", "nevertheless", "to", "purchase", "from", "those", "supplier"]]}, {"text": "We don't even know whether they would want to continue to purchase from them if they had to pay this higher price.", "start": 1398, "stop": 1402.406, "duration": 4.41, "cleanText": [["we", "do", "not", "even", "know", "whether", "they", "would", "want", "to", "continue", "to", "purchase", "from", "them", "if", "they", "have", "to", "pay", "this", "high", "price"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Whether the government would want to.", "start": 1402.406, "stop": 1405.452, "duration": 3.05, "cleanText": [["whether", "the", "government", "would", "want", "to"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1405.452, "stop": 1405.795, "duration": 0.34, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "The government--", "start": 1405.795, "stop": 1406.561, "duration": 0.77, "cleanText": [["the", "government"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "They would say okay, so long, friend.", "start": 1406.561, "stop": 1408.184, "duration": 1.62, "cleanText": [["they", "would", "say", "okay", "so", "long", "friend"]]}, {"text": "If you don't want to sell under this basis, why, that's... take your business some place else.", "start": 1408.184, "stop": 1413.838, "duration": 5.65, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "do", "not", "want", "to", "sell", "under", "this", "basis", "why", "that", "be", "take", "your", "business", "some", "place", "else"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The government, at least in the liquor field, the government... there are only certain entities that sell particular brands.", "start": 1413.838, "stop": 1421.819, "duration": 7.98, "cleanText": [["the", "government", "at", "least", "in", "the", "liquor", "field", "the", "government", "there", "be", "only", "certain", "entity", "that", "sell", "particular", "brand"]]}, {"text": "That's the problem here, one of the problems.", "start": 1421.819, "stop": 1424.771, "duration": 2.95, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "problem", "here", "one", "of", "the", "problem"]]}, {"text": "But there is a second aspect--", "start": 1424.771, "stop": 1425.818, "duration": 1.05, "cleanText": [["but", "there", "be", "a", "second", "aspect"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "You don't need to have a... you don't need to have a full line of whiskey to make--", "start": 1425.818, "stop": 1428.628, "duration": 2.81, "cleanText": [["you", "do", "not", "need", "to", "have", "a", "you", "do", "not", "need", "to", "have", "a", "full", "line", "of", "whiskey", "to", "make"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, the whole point of these enterprises on military bases, they are twofold.", "start": 1428.628, "stop": 1434.079, "duration": 5.45, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "whole", "point", "of", "these", "enterprise", "on", "military", "base", "they", "be", "twofold"]]}, {"text": "One is to provide a service to the servicemen.", "start": 1434.079, "stop": 1436.36, "duration": 2.28, "cleanText": [["one", "be", "to", "provide", "a", "service", "to", "the", "serviceman"]]}, {"text": "And another... and in providing a service you have to provide those products that the consumers demand.", "start": 1436.36, "stop": 1442.045, "duration": 5.69, "cleanText": [["and", "another", "and", "in", "provide", "a", "service", "you", "have", "to", "provide", "those", "product", "that", "the", "consumer", "demand"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--We are arguing about something that really there are no findings about, so--", "start": 1442.045, "stop": 1445.309, "duration": 3.26, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "argue", "about", "something", "that", "really", "there", "be", "no", "finding", "about", "so"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, there is a second aspect to this case that's equally important in terms of its constitutional invalidity.", "start": 1445.309, "stop": 1451.166, "duration": 5.86, "cleanText": [["well", "there", "be", "a", "second", "aspect", "to", "this", "case", "that", "be", "equally", "important", "in", "term", "of", "its", "constitutional", "invalidity"]]}, {"text": "And that is, look at the regulations themselves.", "start": 1451.166, "stop": 1453.698, "duration": 2.53, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "look", "at", "the", "regulation", "themselves"]]}, {"text": "The state tells you it cannot regulate the military's procurement practices, but that is precisely what it is regulations seek to accomplish.", "start": 1453.698, "stop": 1461.1, "duration": 7.4, "cleanText": [["the", "state", "tell", "you", "it", "can", "not", "regulate", "the", "military", "s", "procurement", "practice", "but", "that", "be", "precisely", "what", "it", "be", "regulation", "seek", "to", "accomplish"]]}, {"text": "And under the Supremacy Clause, the state is not at liberty to take that step.", "start": 1461.1, "stop": 1465.598, "duration": 4.5, "cleanText": [["and", "under", "the", "supremacy", "clause", "the", "state", "be", "not", "at", "liberty", "to", "take", "that", "step"]]}, {"text": "And the final problem with these regulations is that since the state is otherwise engaging in regulation over the military's procurement practices, the Twenty-first Amendment in those circumstances, doesn't save the state's regulations from constitutional invalidity.", "start": 1465.598, "stop": 1482.295, "duration": 16.7, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "final", "problem", "with", "these", "regulation", "be", "that", "since", "the", "state", "be", "otherwise", "engage", "in", "regulation", "over", "the", "military", "s", "procurement", "practice", "the", "twenty", "first", "amendment", "in", "those", "circumstance", "do", "not", "save", "the", "state", "s", "regulation", "from", "constitutional", "invalidity"]]}, {"text": "At the outset, Justice Scalia mentioned before, well, what can a state do if there is this problem.", "start": 1482.295, "stop": 1488.621, "duration": 6.33, "cleanText": [["at", "the", "outset", "justice", "scalia", "mention", "before", "well", "what", "can", "a", "state", "do", "if", "there", "be", "this", "problem"]]}, {"text": "Seven states in this country actually use the most efficient method, which is a tax stamp system.", "start": 1488.621, "stop": 1496.43, "duration": 7.81, "cleanText": [["seven", "state", "in", "this", "country", "actually", "use", "the", "most", "efficient", "method", "which", "be", "a", "tax", "stamp", "system"]]}, {"text": "The state could require all licensed wholesalers in the state to affix tax stamps, which would actually be seals on the bottle, on every bottle of liquor that they sell.", "start": 1496.43, "stop": 1505.628, "duration": 9.2, "cleanText": [["the", "state", "could", "require", "all", "licensed", "wholesaler", "in", "the", "state", "to", "affix", "tax", "stamp", "which", "would", "actually", "be", "seal", "on", "the", "bottle", "on", "every", "bottle", "of", "liquor", "that", "they", "sell"]]}, {"text": "The state could then readily determine whether any retailer, or any other person for that matter, were selling untaxed liquor.", "start": 1505.628, "stop": 1512.314, "duration": 6.69, "cleanText": [["the", "state", "could", "then", "readily", "determine", "whether", "any", "retailer", "or", "any", "other", "person", "for", "that", "matter", "we", "be", "sell", "untaxed", "liquor"]]}, {"text": "And in that respect, the states that do that... Minnesota in fact doesn't do that if that is at all relevant, but in that respect there would be no burden on the federal government whatsoever, and how the federal government went about buying its liquor wouldn't affect the efficiency of that system.", "start": 1512.314, "stop": 1528.385, "duration": 16.07, "cleanText": [["and", "in", "that", "respect", "the", "state", "that", "do", "that", "minnesota", "in", "fact", "do", "not", "do", "that", "if", "that", "be", "at", "all", "relevant", "but", "in", "that", "respect", "there", "would", "be", "no", "burden", "on", "the", "federal", "government", "whatsoever", "and", "how", "the", "federal", "government", "go", "about", "buy", "its", "liquor", "would", "not", "affect", "the", "efficiency", "of", "that", "system"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "--But they wouldn't--", "start": 1528.385, "stop": 1529.01, "duration": 0.63, "cleanText": [["but", "they", "would", "not"]]}, {"text": "--But General Spaeth says that doesn't work at Grand Forks because it is on the border.", "start": 1529.01, "stop": 1534.774, "duration": 5.76, "cleanText": [["but", "general", "spaeth", "say", "that", "do", "not", "work", "at", "grand", "fork", "because", "it", "be", "on", "the", "border"]]}, {"text": "Minnesota doesn't require a tax stamp, so you can't tell.", "start": 1534.774, "stop": 1537.476, "duration": 2.7, "cleanText": [["minnesota", "do", "not", "require", "a", "tax", "stamp", "so", "you", "can", "not", "tell"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, he says that, we don't know.", "start": 1537.476, "stop": 1541.021, "duration": 3.54, "cleanText": [["well", "he", "say", "that", "we", "do", "not", "know"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, that is one of the many things we don't know in this case.", "start": 1541.021, "stop": 1544.253, "duration": 3.23, "cleanText": [["well", "that", "be", "one", "of", "the", "many", "thing", "we", "do", "not", "know", "in", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the... there is no doubt that because this case was decided on cross motions for summary judgment the record is quite minimal.", "start": 1544.253, "stop": 1550.517, "duration": 6.26, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "there", "be", "no", "doubt", "that", "because", "this", "case", "be", "decide", "on", "cross", "motion", "for", "summary", "judgment", "the", "record", "be", "quite", "minimal"]]}, {"text": "But we have... there is more here than just--", "start": 1550.517, "stop": 1552.719, "duration": 2.2, "cleanText": [["but", "we", "have", "there", "be", "more", "here", "than", "just"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Excuse me, as far as the Minnesota liquor is concerned, I assume it is a violation of the states law to bring in untaxed liquor, untaxed by North Dakota, whether it is taxed by another state or not.", "start": 1552.719, "stop": 1568.76, "duration": 16.04, "cleanText": [["excuse", "me", "as", "far", "as", "the", "minnesota", "liquor", "be", "concern", "i", "assume", "it", "be", "a", "violation", "of", "the", "state", "law", "to", "bring", "in", "untaxed", "liquor", "untaxed", "by", "north", "dakota", "whether", "it", "be", "tax", "by", "another", "state", "or", "not"]]}, {"text": "Can you--", "start": 1568.76, "stop": 1569.76, "duration": 1, "cleanText": [["can", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--There are allegations--", "start": 1569.76, "stop": 1571.275, "duration": 1.52, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "allegation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I mean, I assume they would want to find all liquor that hasn't paid the state tax, whether it is federal liquor or non-federal liquor.", "start": 1571.275, "stop": 1579.365, "duration": 8.09, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "i", "assume", "they", "would", "want", "to", "find", "all", "liquor", "that", "have", "not", "pay", "the", "state", "tax", "whether", "it", "be", "federal", "liquor", "or", "non", "federal", "liquor"]]}, {"text": "So, the system you suggest would... would be even better than the system that North Dakota has applied.", "start": 1579.365, "stop": 1585.3, "duration": 5.93, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "system", "you", "suggest", "would", "would", "be", "even", "good", "than", "the", "system", "that", "north", "dakota", "have", "apply"]]}, {"text": "It will enable you to identify not only the bootleg federal liquor, but the bootleg Minnesota liquor.", "start": 1585.3, "stop": 1590.142, "duration": 4.84, "cleanText": [["it", "will", "enable", "you", "to", "identify", "not", "only", "the", "bootleg", "federal", "liquor", "but", "the", "bootleg", "minnesota", "liquor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--That is true.", "start": 1590.142, "stop": 1590.642, "duration": 0.5, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "true"]]}, {"text": "And there is another aspect to this case.", "start": 1590.642, "stop": 1592.858, "duration": 2.22, "cleanText": [["and", "there", "be", "another", "aspect", "to", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "In terms of the diversion of liquor, and the government again, because of the limited record, will assume that there is a problem.", "start": 1592.858, "stop": 1599.091, "duration": 6.23, "cleanText": [["in", "term", "of", "the", "diversion", "of", "liquor", "and", "the", "government", "again", "because", "of", "the", "limited", "record", "will", "assume", "that", "there", "be", "a", "problem"]]}, {"text": "And the problem is, as Mr. Spaeth said, bootlegging, the sale... the resale of untaxed liquor.", "start": 1599.091, "stop": 1604.682, "duration": 5.59, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "problem", "be", "as", "mr", "spaeth", "say", "bootlegging", "the", "sale", "the", "resale", "of", "untaxed", "liquor"]]}, {"text": "Assuming that's a problem, liquor on military bases, whether it is bought from out-of-state sources or whether bought from licensed wholesalers in the state, will always be cheaper from liquor off the base in North Dakota.", "start": 1604.682, "stop": 1617.068, "duration": 12.39, "cleanText": [["assume", "that", "be", "a", "problem", "liquor", "on", "military", "base", "whether", "it", "be", "buy", "from", "out", "of", "state", "source", "or", "whether", "buy", "from", "licensed", "wholesaler", "in", "the", "state", "will", "always", "be", "cheap", "from", "liquor", "off", "the", "base", "in", "north", "dakota"]]}, {"text": "And that is not only because of the source, but because liquor sold to the servicemen on the base is not subject to a retail tax.", "start": 1617.068, "stop": 1624.503, "duration": 7.43, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "not", "only", "because", "of", "the", "source", "but", "because", "liquor", "sell", "to", "the", "serviceman", "on", "the", "base", "be", "not", "subject", "to", "a", "retail", "tax"]]}, {"text": "Therefore, under the state's own terms, there is always going to be the potential... potential for diversion, of bootlegging, from the liquor on the base.", "start": 1624.503, "stop": 1632.781, "duration": 8.28, "cleanText": [["therefore", "under", "the", "state", "s", "own", "term", "there", "be", "always", "go", "to", "be", "the", "potential", "potential", "for", "diversion", "of", "bootlegging", "from", "the", "liquor", "on", "the", "base"]]}, {"text": "But what happens here, the state doesn't impose any labeling requirement for liquor sold from the local wholesalers.", "start": 1632.781, "stop": 1639.637, "duration": 6.86, "cleanText": [["but", "what", "happen", "here", "the", "state", "do", "not", "impose", "any", "labeling", "requirement", "for", "liquor", "sell", "from", "the", "local", "wholesaler"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "I suppose that also there is probably not as high a mark up on the base either.", "start": 1639.637, "stop": 1642.729, "duration": 3.09, "cleanText": [["i", "suppose", "that", "also", "there", "be", "probably", "not", "as", "high", "a", "mark", "up", "on", "the", "base", "either"]]}, {"text": "But, Mr. Lazerwitz, has the federal government ever required the bases to label the stuff, or to require the supplier to but a base on it... a label on it indicating it is tax-free liquor?", "start": 1642.729, "stop": 1651.819, "duration": 9.09, "cleanText": [["but", "mr", "lazerwitz", "have", "the", "federal", "government", "ever", "require", "the", "base", "to", "label", "the", "stuff", "or", "to", "require", "the", "supplier", "to", "but", "a", "base", "on", "it", "a", "label", "on", "it", "indicate", "it", "be", "tax", "free", "liquor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Not that I know of, although the military, the Department of Defense, has a specific regulation telling the servicemen that you cannot... we will sell you the liquor on the base, but if you take it off the base you are subject to state law.", "start": 1651.819, "stop": 1664.611, "duration": 12.79, "cleanText": [["not", "that", "i", "know", "of", "although", "the", "military", "the", "department", "of", "defense", "have", "a", "specific", "regulation", "tell", "the", "serviceman", "that", "you", "can", "not", "we", "will", "sell", "you", "the", "liquor", "on", "the", "base", "but", "if", "you", "take", "it", "off", "the", "base", "you", "be", "subject", "to", "state", "law"]]}, {"text": "And they are certainly told and it's enforced, not to resell this to unauthorized personnel.", "start": 1664.611, "stop": 1669.828, "duration": 5.22, "cleanText": [["and", "they", "be", "certainly", "told", "and", "it", "be", "enforce", "not", "to", "resell", "this", "to", "unauthorized", "personnel"]]}, {"text": "You and your wife can have a drink, but you can't sell it to your buddy off the base, or to anyone else.", "start": 1669.828, "stop": 1675.935, "duration": 6.11, "cleanText": [["you", "and", "your", "wife", "can", "have", "a", "drink", "but", "you", "can", "not", "sell", "it", "to", "your", "buddy", "off", "the", "base", "or", "to", "anyone", "else"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, but you can take it home.", "start": 1675.935, "stop": 1676.419, "duration": 0.48, "cleanText": [["no", "but", "you", "can", "take", "it", "home"]]}, {"text": "Would it be impossible for the federal government to affix the... spend the three cents and fixing these labels on.", "start": 1676.419, "stop": 1682.136, "duration": 5.72, "cleanText": [["would", "it", "be", "impossible", "for", "the", "federal", "government", "to", "affix", "the", "spend", "the", "three", "cent", "and", "fix", "these", "label", "on"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, of course not.", "start": 1682.136, "stop": 1682.604, "duration": 0.47, "cleanText": [["oh", "of", "course", "not"]]}, {"text": "We could easily do it, but there, but the state can't tell us to do it.", "start": 1682.604, "stop": 1685.681, "duration": 3.08, "cleanText": [["we", "could", "easily", "do", "it", "but", "there", "but", "the", "state", "can", "not", "tell", "us", "to", "do", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "The state can't make you do it.", "start": 1685.681, "stop": 1685.947, "duration": 0.27, "cleanText": [["the", "state", "can", "not", "make", "you", "do", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "And the state has told us in its brief that it can't tell us to do it.", "start": 1685.947, "stop": 1689.977, "duration": 4.03, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "state", "have", "tell", "us", "in", "its", "brief", "that", "it", "can", "not", "tell", "us", "to", "do", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "But you could presumably satisfy... if you were willing to go to that burden, you could probably get the liquor.", "start": 1689.977, "stop": 1693.959, "duration": 3.98, "cleanText": [["but", "you", "could", "presumably", "satisfy", "if", "you", "we", "be", "willing", "to", "go", "to", "that", "burden", "you", "could", "probably", "get", "the", "liquor"]]}, {"text": "If the supplier won't sell it because of the burden, you could probably get it by paying a three cents a bottle.", "start": 1693.959, "stop": 1699.847, "duration": 5.89, "cleanText": [["if", "the", "supplier", "will", "not", "sell", "it", "because", "of", "the", "burden", "you", "could", "probably", "get", "it", "by", "pay", "a", "three", "cent", "a", "bottle"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Actually, no.", "start": 1699.847, "stop": 1700.488, "duration": 0.64, "cleanText": [["actually", "no"]]}, {"text": "In this case we couldn't, because the state regulation, as explained to the distillers, requires them to put the label on before it comes into the state.", "start": 1700.488, "stop": 1709.812, "duration": 9.32, "cleanText": [["in", "this", "case", "we", "could", "not", "because", "the", "state", "regulation", "as", "explain", "to", "the", "distiller", "require", "them", "to", "put", "the", "label", "on", "before", "it", "come", "into", "the", "state"]]}, {"text": "And that is what scared off the distillers and the suppliers.", "start": 1709.812, "stop": 1712.592, "duration": 2.78, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "what", "scar", "off", "the", "distiller", "and", "the", "supplier"]]}, {"text": "If in fact the regulation were any liquor... I mean, the problem with the state, the state's difficulty is, if they want us to put the label on once it gets into the state, they can't tell us to do that.", "start": 1712.592, "stop": 1725.508, "duration": 12.92, "cleanText": [["if", "in", "fact", "the", "regulation", "we", "be", "any", "liquor", "i", "mean", "the", "problem", "with", "the", "state", "the", "state", "s", "difficulty", "be", "if", "they", "want", "us", "to", "put", "the", "label", "on", "once", "it", "get", "into", "the", "state", "they", "can", "not", "tell", "us", "to", "do", "that"]]}, {"text": "And it also won't accomplish what in fact is going on here, which is to change the way the military buys its liquor.", "start": 1725.508, "stop": 1730.804, "duration": 5.3, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "also", "will", "not", "accomplish", "what", "in", "fact", "be", "go", "on", "here", "which", "be", "to", "change", "the", "way", "the", "military", "buy", "its", "liquor"]]}, {"text": "And that's... that is our second point.", "start": 1730.804, "stop": 1733.819, "duration": 3.01, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "that", "be", "our", "second", "point"]]}, {"text": "It is not simply the problem with the increased cost.", "start": 1733.819, "stop": 1737.644, "duration": 3.83, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "simply", "the", "problem", "with", "the", "increase", "cost"]]}, {"text": "What the state is doing here is the Paul case, is the Leslie Miller case, is the Public Utilities Commission case.", "start": 1737.644, "stop": 1743.626, "duration": 5.98, "cleanText": [["what", "the", "state", "be", "do", "here", "be", "the", "paul", "case", "be", "the", "leslie", "miller", "case", "be", "the", "public", "utility", "commission", "case"]]}, {"text": "It doesn't matter that the regulation by its terms doesn't apply directly to us.", "start": 1743.626, "stop": 1748.749, "duration": 5.12, "cleanText": [["it", "do", "not", "matter", "that", "the", "regulation", "by", "its", "term", "do", "not", "apply", "directly", "to", "us"]]}, {"text": "In fact, this regulation is even worse than the regulations at issue in those cases because those cases, in Leslie Miller, Paul, and the Public Utilities Commission cases, those were general regulations that applied to anyone, any firm.", "start": 1748.749, "stop": 1761.993, "duration": 13.24, "cleanText": [["in", "fact", "this", "regulation", "be", "even", "bad", "than", "the", "regulation", "at", "issue", "in", "those", "case", "because", "those", "case", "in", "leslie", "miller", "paul", "and", "the", "public", "utility", "commission", "case", "those", "we", "be", "general", "regulation", "that", "apply", "to", "anyone", "any", "firm"]]}, {"text": "And there, those firms got caught up in the net because they did business with the government.", "start": 1761.993, "stop": 1767.429, "duration": 5.44, "cleanText": [["and", "there", "those", "firm", "get", "catch", "up", "in", "the", "net", "because", "they", "do", "business", "with", "the", "government"]]}, {"text": "This regulation, on its face, tells us who it is seeking to regulate.", "start": 1767.429, "stop": 1771.381, "duration": 3.95, "cleanText": [["this", "regulation", "on", "its", "face", "tell", "us", "who", "it", "be", "seek", "to", "regulate"]]}, {"text": "It is seeking to regulate the transaction between the federal government and its suppliers.", "start": 1771.381, "stop": 1776.519, "duration": 5.14, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "seek", "to", "regulate", "the", "transaction", "between", "the", "federal", "government", "and", "its", "supplier"]]}, {"text": "It is limited just to the people that do business with us.", "start": 1776.519, "stop": 1778.972, "duration": 2.45, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "limited", "just", "to", "the", "people", "that", "do", "business", "with", "us"]]}, {"text": "So, a fortiori it is even more suspect in terms of those cases.", "start": 1778.972, "stop": 1784.408, "duration": 5.44, "cleanText": [["so", "a", "fortiori", "it", "be", "even", "more", "suspect", "in", "term", "of", "those", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Could the state impose a general sales or use tax on these sales?", "start": 1784.408, "stop": 1789.373, "duration": 4.97, "cleanText": [["could", "the", "state", "impose", "a", "general", "sale", "or", "use", "tax", "on", "these", "sale"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "They could not.", "start": 1789.373, "stop": 1790.638, "duration": 1.26, "cleanText": [["they", "could", "not"]]}, {"text": "That is the Mississippi case, the Mississippi cases.", "start": 1790.638, "stop": 1794.652, "duration": 4.01, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "mississippi", "case", "the", "mississippi", "case"]]}, {"text": "And so I disagree with Mr. Spaeth when he suggests that he... they could readily do this another way.", "start": 1794.652, "stop": 1799.29, "duration": 4.64, "cleanText": [["and", "so", "i", "disagree", "with", "mr", "spaeth", "when", "he", "suggest", "that", "he", "they", "could", "readily", "do", "this", "another", "way"]]}, {"text": "If they... if the state wants to increase local tax revenue they cannot do that at the expense of the government's procurement of liquor.", "start": 1799.29, "stop": 1806.788, "duration": 7.5, "cleanText": [["if", "they", "if", "the", "state", "want", "to", "increase", "local", "tax", "revenue", "they", "can", "not", "do", "that", "at", "the", "expense", "of", "the", "government", "s", "procurement", "of", "liquor"]]}, {"text": "That is precisely what this Court held in the two Mississippi tax cases.", "start": 1806.788, "stop": 1811.052, "duration": 4.26, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "precisely", "what", "this", "court", "hold", "in", "the", "two", "mississippi", "tax", "case"]]}, {"text": "What... my point at the beginning with the problem, we... this case is not about the United States trying to disable North Dakota or any other state from policing a legitimate problem.", "start": 1811.052, "stop": 1823.766, "duration": 12.71, "cleanText": [["what", "my", "point", "at", "the", "beginning", "with", "the", "problem", "we", "this", "case", "be", "not", "about", "the", "united", "state", "try", "to", "disable", "north", "dakota", "or", "any", "other", "state", "from", "police", "a", "legitimate", "problem"]]}, {"text": "But there are ways to do it that have nothing to do with interfering with what states can't do, and that is regulate military procurement.", "start": 1823.766, "stop": 1831.122, "duration": 7.36, "cleanText": [["but", "there", "be", "way", "to", "do", "it", "that", "have", "nothing", "to", "do", "with", "interfere", "with", "what", "state", "can", "not", "do", "and", "that", "be", "regulate", "military", "procurement"]]}, {"text": "In terms of the dollars, the practical effects are we wouldn't bring lawsuits if the dollars didn't matter.", "start": 1831.122, "stop": 1837.712, "duration": 6.59, "cleanText": [["in", "term", "of", "the", "dollar", "the", "practical", "effect", "be", "we", "would", "not", "bring", "lawsuit", "if", "the", "dollar", "do", "not", "matter"]]}, {"text": "But here the legislative record, and I mentioned before Title... Section 2488, Congress considered all these... this precise matter.", "start": 1837.712, "stop": 1848.178, "duration": 10.47, "cleanText": [["but", "here", "the", "legislative", "record", "and", "i", "mention", "before", "title", "section", "congress", "consider", "all", "these", "this", "precise", "matter"]]}, {"text": "Congress has told the military, look, we want you to buy beer and wine for the bases only from in-state.", "start": 1848.178, "stop": 1854.66, "duration": 6.48, "cleanText": [["congress", "have", "tell", "the", "military", "look", "we", "want", "you", "to", "buy", "beer", "and", "wine", "for", "the", "base", "only", "from", "in", "state"]]}, {"text": "But when it comes to liquor, we want you to buy it from wherever you can get it at the cheapest to save money.", "start": 1854.66, "stop": 1860.923, "duration": 6.26, "cleanText": [["but", "when", "it", "come", "to", "liquor", "we", "want", "you", "to", "buy", "it", "from", "wherever", "you", "can", "get", "it", "at", "the", "cheap", "to", "save", "money"]]}, {"text": "And we need the money because Congress doesn't fund what the profits of these sales go for.", "start": 1860.923, "stop": 1865.937, "duration": 5.01, "cleanText": [["and", "we", "need", "the", "money", "because", "congress", "do", "not", "fund", "what", "the", "profit", "of", "these", "sale", "go", "for"]]}, {"text": "And it is things like child care centers, libraries, photo labs, bowling alleys, the things on the military bases that are for the servicemen's benefit.", "start": 1865.937, "stop": 1874.855, "duration": 8.92, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "be", "thing", "like", "child", "care", "center", "library", "photo", "lab", "bowl", "alley", "the", "thing", "on", "the", "military", "base", "that", "be", "for", "the", "serviceman", "s", "benefit"]]}, {"text": "And so this is important in that respect.", "start": 1874.855, "stop": 1877.837, "duration": 2.98, "cleanText": [["and", "so", "this", "be", "important", "in", "that", "respect"]]}, {"text": "This money is important.", "start": 1877.837, "stop": 1879.805, "duration": 1.97, "cleanText": [["this", "money", "be", "important"]]}, {"text": "Going back to the suggestion that is made in the brief, and it was mentioned here, that perhaps the military can just absorb the cost; we could just raise our prices if it costs us more to buy liquor.", "start": 1879.805, "stop": 1890.443, "duration": 10.64, "cleanText": [["go", "back", "to", "the", "suggestion", "that", "be", "make", "in", "the", "brief", "and", "it", "be", "mention", "here", "that", "perhaps", "the", "military", "can", "just", "absorb", "the", "cost", "we", "could", "just", "raise", "our", "price", "if", "it", "cost", "us", "more", "to", "buy", "liquor"]]}, {"text": "In fact, there is a Department of Defense regulation in deference to states and local... and other local liquor sale... entities, we will not sell liquor below 10 percent of the shelf price in any local market.", "start": 1890.443, "stop": 1904.062, "duration": 13.62, "cleanText": [["in", "fact", "there", "be", "a", "department", "of", "defense", "regulation", "in", "deference", "to", "state", "and", "local", "and", "other", "local", "liquor", "sale", "entity", "we", "will", "not", "sell", "liquor", "below", "percent", "of", "the", "shelf", "price", "in", "any", "local", "market"]]}, {"text": "So, the military works with an effective 10 percent profit margin.", "start": 1904.062, "stop": 1908.293, "duration": 4.23, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "military", "work", "with", "an", "effective", "percent", "profit", "margin"]]}, {"text": "Obviously we can't sell above the local price, one, because it makes no economic sense and, two, the entity that runs these shops now, the Army and Air Force Exchange Service, by regulation, its mission is to provide cheaper goods to servicemen.", "start": 1908.293, "stop": 1923.506, "duration": 15.21, "cleanText": [["obviously", "we", "can", "not", "sell", "above", "the", "local", "price", "one", "because", "it", "make", "no", "economic", "sense", "and", "two", "the", "entity", "that", "run", "these", "shop", "now", "the", "army", "and", "air", "force", "exchange", "service", "by", "regulation", "its", "mission", "be", "to", "provide", "cheap", "good", "to", "serviceman"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "And you... that is a 10 percent profit margin, assuming you had to pay the same rent for stores and everything else.", "start": 1923.506, "stop": 1931.426, "duration": 7.92, "cleanText": [["and", "you", "that", "be", "a", "percent", "profit", "margin", "assume", "you", "have", "to", "pay", "the", "same", "rent", "for", "store", "and", "everything", "else"]]}, {"text": "I mean, you're leaving out of that the fact that you are not only selling lower, but you have... you have fewer costs.", "start": 1931.426, "stop": 1937.548, "duration": 6.12, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "you", "be", "leave", "out", "of", "that", "the", "fact", "that", "you", "be", "not", "only", "sell", "low", "but", "you", "have", "you", "have", "few", "cost"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, I don't want to downplay the competitive advantages of military procurement, but I just don't want to leave the Court with the impression that we had a simple option of just raising prices.", "start": 1937.548, "stop": 1948.559, "duration": 11.01, "cleanText": [["oh", "i", "do", "not", "want", "to", "downplay", "the", "competitive", "advantage", "of", "military", "procurement", "but", "i", "just", "do", "not", "want", "to", "leave", "the", "court", "with", "the", "impression", "that", "we", "have", "a", "simple", "option", "of", "just", "raise", "price"]]}, {"text": "The fact of the matter is, the military got very smart.", "start": 1948.559, "stop": 1952.744, "duration": 4.18, "cleanText": [["the", "fact", "of", "the", "matter", "be", "the", "military", "get", "very", "smart"]]}, {"text": "It used to buy liquor, a lot of liquor, in-state from the distributors and paid the additional mark up that is the result of the local tax.", "start": 1952.744, "stop": 1960.913, "duration": 8.17, "cleanText": [["it", "use", "to", "buy", "liquor", "a", "lot", "of", "liquor", "in", "state", "from", "the", "distributor", "and", "pay", "the", "additional", "mark", "up", "that", "be", "the", "result", "of", "the", "local", "tax"]]}, {"text": "Well, the military became smarter, and said look, if we can buy this in bulk quantities we are going to save a lot of money, and that is what the military does.", "start": 1960.913, "stop": 1969.191, "duration": 8.28, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "military", "become", "smarter", "and", "say", "look", "if", "we", "can", "buy", "this", "in", "bulk", "quantity", "we", "be", "go", "to", "save", "a", "lot", "of", "money", "and", "that", "be", "what", "the", "military", "do"]]}, {"text": "And it saves a lot of money.", "start": 1969.191, "stop": 1970.252, "duration": 1.06, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "save", "a", "lot", "of", "money"]]}, {"text": "And regulations like this, that effectively take out certain source suppliers of a market, affects us.", "start": 1970.252, "stop": 1977.906, "duration": 7.65, "cleanText": [["and", "regulation", "like", "this", "that", "effectively", "take", "out", "certain", "source", "supplier", "of", "a", "market", "affect", "us"]]}, {"text": "And it ruins the way we do our business.", "start": 1977.906, "stop": 1980.374, "duration": 2.47, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "ruin", "the", "way", "we", "do", "our", "business"]]}, {"text": "And that is the problem.", "start": 1980.374, "stop": 1981.374, "duration": 1, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "the", "problem"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, but it is also true, I suppose, that they... to the extent that there is liquor bootlegged off the base in large volumes, you get the benefit of that by increased sales and increased profit to support your day care centers.", "start": 1981.374, "stop": 1992.838, "duration": 11.46, "cleanText": [["yes", "but", "it", "be", "also", "true", "i", "suppose", "that", "they", "to", "the", "extent", "that", "there", "be", "liquor", "bootleg", "off", "the", "base", "in", "large", "volume", "you", "get", "the", "benefit", "of", "that", "by", "increase", "sale", "and", "increased", "profit", "to", "support", "your", "day", "care", "center"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well--", "start": 1992.838, "stop": 1993.431, "duration": 0.59, "cleanText": [["well"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "So you actually have a financial interest in having the state law violated, in the way they are complaining about it.", "start": 1993.431, "stop": 1997.898, "duration": 4.47, "cleanText": [["so", "you", "actually", "have", "a", "financial", "interest", "in", "have", "the", "state", "law", "violate", "in", "the", "way", "they", "be", "complain", "about", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, no, we don't, Justice Stevens, and there are some practical concerns.", "start": 1997.898, "stop": 2001.037, "duration": 3.14, "cleanText": [["well", "no", "we", "do", "not", "justice", "stevens", "and", "there", "be", "some", "practical", "concern"]]}, {"text": "One is, we have rules, and we don't want... and military bases are in communities and in states, and the last thing the military wants is for state governments to yell and complain that the military is running a bootleg operation, because that is going to affect how it does its business.", "start": 2001.037, "stop": 2018.952, "duration": 17.91, "cleanText": [["one", "be", "we", "have", "rule", "and", "we", "do", "not", "want", "and", "military", "base", "be", "in", "community", "and", "in", "state", "and", "the", "last", "thing", "the", "military", "want", "be", "for", "state", "government", "to", "yell", "and", "complain", "that", "the", "military", "be", "run", "a", "bootleg", "operation", "because", "that", "be", "go", "to", "affect", "how", "it", "do", "its", "business"]]}, {"text": "It makes... it's no... it doesn't make any business sense--", "start": 2018.952, "stop": 2021.311, "duration": 2.36, "cleanText": [["it", "make", "it", "be", "no", "it", "do", "not", "make", "any", "business", "sense"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "It may not, but if its, if the figures he has given us are correct--", "start": 2021.311, "stop": 2025.107, "duration": 3.8, "cleanText": [["it", "may", "not", "but", "if", "its", "if", "the", "figure", "he", "have", "give", "us", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, the--", "start": 2025.107, "stop": 2025.513, "duration": 0.41, "cleanText": [["well", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "--it is apparently a serious problem that the Commander of the base should have been able to see was going on out there.", "start": 2025.513, "stop": 2030.712, "duration": 5.2, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "apparently", "a", "serious", "problem", "that", "the", "commander", "of", "the", "base", "should", "have", "be", "able", "to", "see", "be", "go", "on", "out", "there"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, the example in Hawaii was, I believe it is Hawaii, it is so silly, but the money, the liquor was stolen from the military.", "start": 2030.712, "stop": 2037.289, "duration": 6.58, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "example", "in", "hawaii", "be", "i", "believe", "it", "be", "hawaii", "it", "be", "so", "silly", "but", "the", "money", "the", "liquor", "be", "steal", "from", "the", "military"]]}, {"text": "I mean, there are instances where people, the truckers, stop off at a highway before getting to the base and sell the liquor.", "start": 2037.289, "stop": 2042.958, "duration": 5.67, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "there", "be", "instance", "where", "people", "the", "trucker", "stop", "off", "at", "a", "highway", "before", "get", "to", "the", "base", "and", "sell", "the", "liquor"]]}, {"text": "Now that is, we don't like that either.", "start": 2042.958, "stop": 2044.817, "duration": 1.86, "cleanText": [["now", "that", "be", "we", "do", "not", "like", "that", "either"]]}, {"text": "That is something we call in the FBI about.", "start": 2044.817, "stop": 2046.692, "duration": 1.88, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "something", "we", "call", "in", "the", "fbi", "about"]]}, {"text": "There is no doubt that there is always going to be the chance of someone buying liquor on the base for $9, and it sells in the local store for $11, becoming an enterprising serviceman and sell it to his buddy for $10.", "start": 2046.692, "stop": 2060.202, "duration": 13.51, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "doubt", "that", "there", "be", "always", "go", "to", "be", "the", "chance", "of", "someone", "buy", "liquor", "on", "the", "base", "for", "and", "it", "sell", "in", "the", "local", "store", "for", "become", "an", "enterprising", "serviceman", "and", "sell", "it", "to", "his", "buddy", "for"]]}, {"text": "That is, that is always going happen.", "start": 2060.202, "stop": 2062.685, "duration": 2.48, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "that", "be", "always", "go", "happen"]]}, {"text": "And what we do, and this is what the court of appeals suggested, and I think there is a lot of sense to it, he said instead of litigating these things, and instead of thinking up ways to try to travel through the cases and spend all these years litigating, why don't we just cooperate.", "start": 2062.685, "stop": 2077.427, "duration": 14.74, "cleanText": [["and", "what", "we", "do", "and", "this", "be", "what", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "suggest", "and", "i", "think", "there", "be", "a", "lot", "of", "sense", "to", "it", "he", "say", "instead", "of", "litigate", "these", "thing", "and", "instead", "of", "think", "up", "way", "to", "try", "to", "travel", "through", "the", "case", "and", "spend", "all", "these", "year", "litigate", "why", "do", "not", "we", "just", "cooperate"]]}, {"text": "And there are ways to cooperate without litigating something like this.", "start": 2077.427, "stop": 2080.739, "duration": 3.31, "cleanText": [["and", "there", "be", "way", "to", "cooperate", "without", "litigate", "something", "like", "this"]]}, {"text": "And the fact that the military, by its regulations, says look, we will cooperate with state authorities.", "start": 2080.739, "stop": 2086.502, "duration": 5.76, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "fact", "that", "the", "military", "by", "its", "regulation", "say", "look", "we", "will", "cooperate", "with", "state", "authority"]]}, {"text": "We don't want bootlegging; it is not in our interest.", "start": 2086.502, "stop": 2089.391, "duration": 2.89, "cleanText": [["we", "do", "not", "want", "bootlegging", "it", "be", "not", "in", "our", "interest"]]}, {"text": "We... and there are also other things the military can do.", "start": 2089.391, "stop": 2092.734, "duration": 3.34, "cleanText": [["we", "and", "there", "be", "also", "other", "thing", "the", "military", "can", "do"]]}, {"text": "If, in fact, someone is known to be a bootlegger... that's sort of an odd word, but his privileges can be lifted.", "start": 2092.734, "stop": 2102.169, "duration": 9.43, "cleanText": [["if", "in", "fact", "someone", "be", "know", "to", "be", "a", "bootlegger", "that", "be", "sort", "of", "an", "odd", "word", "but", "his", "privilege", "can", "be", "lift"]]}, {"text": "He can certainly be punished by the military if he is a serviceman if he is breaking--", "start": 2102.169, "stop": 2105.621, "duration": 3.45, "cleanText": [["he", "can", "certainly", "be", "punish", "by", "the", "military", "if", "he", "be", "a", "serviceman", "if", "he", "be", "break"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Who's supposed to read these labels, do you suppose?", "start": 2105.621, "stop": 2110.26, "duration": 4.64, "cleanText": [["who", "be", "suppose", "to", "read", "these", "label", "do", "you", "suppose"]]}, {"text": "Who does the state want to read those labels?", "start": 2110.26, "stop": 2112.898, "duration": 2.64, "cleanText": [["who", "do", "the", "state", "want", "to", "read", "those", "label"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, I think the way the regulations are set up, they don't, they could care less.", "start": 2112.898, "stop": 2116.724, "duration": 3.83, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think", "the", "way", "the", "regulation", "be", "set", "up", "they", "do", "not", "they", "could", "care", "less"]]}, {"text": "Because in fact--", "start": 2116.724, "stop": 2117.521, "duration": 0.8, "cleanText": [["because", "in", "fact"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yeah, but they... so, do they think this is really going to be an effective way of curing their problem?", "start": 2117.521, "stop": 2124.55, "duration": 7.03, "cleanText": [["yeah", "but", "they", "so", "do", "they", "think", "this", "be", "really", "go", "to", "be", "an", "effective", "way", "of", "cure", "their", "problem"]]}, {"text": "Because, after all... all the label does is repeat what is in the military law--", "start": 2124.55, "stop": 2129.642, "duration": 5.09, "cleanText": [["because", "after", "all", "all", "the", "label", "do", "be", "repeat", "what", "be", "in", "the", "military", "law"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, I--", "start": 2129.642, "stop": 2130.016, "duration": 0.37, "cleanText": [["well", "i"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--don't sell off the base, don't use off the base.", "start": 2130.016, "stop": 2133.093, "duration": 3.08, "cleanText": [["do", "not", "sell", "off", "the", "base", "do", "not", "use", "off", "the", "base"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, one curious aspect of this case, and I am not sure it's my province to get into, but the only, if you read North Dakota's laws, there is no law that says it's illegal to consume liquor off the base.", "start": 2133.093, "stop": 2146.213, "duration": 13.12, "cleanText": [["well", "one", "curious", "aspect", "of", "this", "case", "and", "i", "be", "not", "sure", "it", "be", "my", "province", "to", "get", "into", "but", "the", "only", "if", "you", "read", "north", "dakota", "s", "law", "there", "be", "no", "law", "that", "say", "it", "be", "illegal", "to", "consume", "liquor", "off", "the", "base"]]}, {"text": "The only law cited in this case, and it is actually by the amicus briefs, is that provision of the administrative code saying that all liquor imported into the state must be imported through a licensed wholesaler.", "start": 2146.213, "stop": 2158.63, "duration": 12.42, "cleanText": [["the", "only", "law", "cite", "in", "this", "case", "and", "it", "be", "actually", "by", "the", "amicus", "brief", "be", "that", "provision", "of", "the", "administrative", "code", "say", "that", "all", "liquor", "import", "into", "the", "state", "must", "be", "import", "through", "a", "licensed", "wholesaler"]]}, {"text": "Now, the state tells us that it is illegal for a serviceman to have untaxed liquor off base.", "start": 2158.63, "stop": 2164.127, "duration": 5.5, "cleanText": [["now", "the", "state", "tell", "us", "that", "it", "be", "illegal", "for", "a", "serviceman", "to", "have", "untaxed", "liquor", "off", "base"]]}, {"text": "We can't dispute that, if that is what the state is now saying.", "start": 2164.127, "stop": 2168.188, "duration": 4.06, "cleanText": [["we", "can", "not", "dispute", "that", "if", "that", "be", "what", "the", "state", "be", "now", "say"]]}, {"text": "But there are no penalties if--", "start": 2168.188, "stop": 2170.11, "duration": 1.92, "cleanText": [["but", "there", "be", "no", "penalty", "if"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, do you think there... I would think, I would think if this... putting on this label is not an effective way of curing the problem they want to cure, that you would argue that.", "start": 2170.11, "stop": 2180.839, "duration": 10.73, "cleanText": [["well", "do", "you", "think", "there", "i", "would", "think", "i", "would", "think", "if", "this", "put", "on", "this", "label", "be", "not", "an", "effective", "way", "of", "cure", "the", "problem", "they", "want", "to", "cure", "that", "you", "would", "argue", "that"]]}, {"text": "Do you think this is... let's assume there is a problem.", "start": 2180.839, "stop": 2184.229, "duration": 3.39, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "think", "this", "be", "let", "us", "assume", "there", "be", "a", "problem"]]}, {"text": "Do you think the labeling is an effective way of curing it?", "start": 2184.229, "stop": 2186.791, "duration": 2.56, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "think", "the", "labeling", "be", "an", "effective", "way", "of", "cure", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The labeling would be... no, it is an incomplete way, and it is an incomplete way for the reason I gave before.", "start": 2186.791, "stop": 2192.334, "duration": 5.54, "cleanText": [["the", "labeling", "would", "be", "no", "it", "be", "an", "incomplete", "way", "and", "it", "be", "an", "incomplete", "way", "for", "the", "reason", "i", "give", "before"]]}, {"text": "The state doesn't require any labeling for those... we do buy, just for the Court's information, in North Dakota we do buy some liquor from in-state sources.", "start": 2192.334, "stop": 2200.831, "duration": 8.5, "cleanText": [["the", "state", "do", "not", "require", "any", "labeling", "for", "those", "we", "do", "buy", "just", "for", "the", "court", "s", "information", "in", "north", "dakota", "we", "do", "buy", "some", "liquor", "from", "in", "state", "source"]]}, {"text": "We don't buy all of it from our warehouse, it is not all shipped to our warehouse.", "start": 2200.831, "stop": 2204.83, "duration": 4, "cleanText": [["we", "do", "not", "buy", "all", "of", "it", "from", "our", "warehouse", "it", "be", "not", "all", "ship", "to", "our", "warehouse"]]}, {"text": "And so the reason it is an ineffective requirement is there is no label on those... on those, first of all, on the beer and wine.", "start": 2204.83, "stop": 2211.921, "duration": 7.09, "cleanText": [["and", "so", "the", "reason", "it", "be", "an", "ineffective", "requirement", "be", "there", "be", "no", "label", "on", "those", "on", "those", "first", "of", "all", "on", "the", "beer", "and", "wine"]]}, {"text": "There is no label on the beer and wine.", "start": 2211.921, "stop": 2213.561, "duration": 1.64, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "label", "on", "the", "beer", "and", "wine"]]}, {"text": "And it is always going to be cheaper on the base.", "start": 2213.561, "stop": 2215.309, "duration": 1.75, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "be", "always", "go", "to", "be", "cheap", "on", "the", "base"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "But for the state to think this is going to cure their problem, somebody has to read the label and say gee, I had better obey what this label says.", "start": 2215.309, "stop": 2222.026, "duration": 6.72, "cleanText": [["but", "for", "the", "state", "to", "think", "this", "be", "go", "to", "cure", "their", "problem", "somebody", "have", "to", "read", "the", "label", "and", "say", "gee", "i", "have", "well", "obey", "what", "this", "label", "say"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the servicemen are told--", "start": 2222.026, "stop": 2223.714, "duration": 1.69, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "serviceman", "be", "tell"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "But that is no different than what the military already requires.", "start": 2223.714, "stop": 2229.039, "duration": 5.33, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "be", "no", "different", "than", "what", "the", "military", "already", "require"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--We tell the servicemen that we'll sell it to you, but if you take it off the base you are subject to state law.", "start": 2229.039, "stop": 2235.208, "duration": 6.17, "cleanText": [["we", "tell", "the", "serviceman", "that", "we", "will", "sell", "it", "to", "you", "but", "if", "you", "take", "it", "off", "the", "base", "you", "be", "subject", "to", "state", "law"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I guess the state wants to be able to identify these bottles off base, if they should come across a cache of liquor in a barn.", "start": 2235.208, "stop": 2242.611, "duration": 7.4, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "guess", "the", "state", "want", "to", "be", "able", "to", "identify", "these", "bottle", "off", "base", "if", "they", "should", "come", "across", "a", "cache", "of", "liquor", "in", "a", "barn"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, sure, or--", "start": 2242.611, "stop": 2243.158, "duration": 0.55, "cleanText": [["oh", "sure", "or"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "For example, say ah ha, this is untaxed liquor, I see these little orange labels on it which you can't get off.", "start": 2243.158, "stop": 2248.249, "duration": 5.09, "cleanText": [["for", "example", "say", "ah", "ha", "this", "be", "untaxed", "liquor", "i", "see", "these", "little", "orange", "label", "on", "it", "which", "you", "can", "not", "get", "off"]]}, {"text": "I assume that that is the purpose of it, isn't it, to identify the bottles--", "start": 2248.249, "stop": 2251.045, "duration": 2.8, "cleanText": [["i", "assume", "that", "that", "be", "the", "purpose", "of", "it", "be", "not", "it", "to", "identify", "the", "bottle"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes, and also... I mean, the example cited in Washington where someone was essentially selling to another liquor store.", "start": 2251.045, "stop": 2256.028, "duration": 4.98, "cleanText": [["yes", "and", "also", "i", "mean", "the", "example", "cite", "in", "washington", "where", "someone", "be", "essentially", "sell", "to", "another", "liquor", "store"]]}, {"text": "You could... a state liquor inspector could walk through a liquor store, go through the inventory and say well, there is no label on this, where did you get it from?", "start": 2256.028, "stop": 2263.478, "duration": 7.45, "cleanText": [["you", "could", "a", "state", "liquor", "inspector", "could", "walk", "through", "a", "liquor", "store", "go", "through", "the", "inventory", "and", "say", "well", "there", "be", "no", "label", "on", "this", "where", "do", "you", "get", "it", "from"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, I suppose it is also not implausible to assume that the sticker requirement is so burdensome that you will have to buy through the local wholesaler.", "start": 2263.478, "stop": 2270.367, "duration": 6.89, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "suppose", "it", "be", "also", "not", "implausible", "to", "assume", "that", "the", "sticker", "requirement", "be", "so", "burdensome", "that", "you", "will", "have", "to", "buy", "through", "the", "local", "wholesaler"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "It certainly... anyone who knows the liquor business would know that you would.", "start": 2270.367, "stop": 2274.49, "duration": 4.12, "cleanText": [["it", "certainly", "anyone", "who", "know", "the", "liquor", "business", "would", "know", "that", "you", "would"]]}, {"text": "And I'll... I can explain to the Court... I mean, this is the reason, and Justice Kennedy alluded to it before.", "start": 2274.49, "stop": 2280.066, "duration": 5.58, "cleanText": [["and", "I", "will", "i", "can", "explain", "to", "the", "court", "i", "mean", "this", "be", "the", "reason", "and", "justice", "kennedy", "allude", "to", "it", "before"]]}, {"text": "The labels, of course, are so innocuous looking and they are so cheap, but it's breaking down the packaging.", "start": 2280.066, "stop": 2286.843, "duration": 6.78, "cleanText": [["the", "label", "of", "course", "be", "so", "innocuous", "look", "and", "they", "be", "so", "cheap", "but", "it", "be", "break", "down", "the", "packaging"]]}, {"text": "A lot of liquor comes directly from overseas.", "start": 2286.843, "stop": 2289.263, "duration": 2.42, "cleanText": [["a", "lot", "of", "liquor", "come", "directly", "from", "overseas"]]}, {"text": "It is packaged overseas.", "start": 2289.263, "stop": 2291.341, "duration": 2.08, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "package", "overseas"]]}, {"text": "If the... if the distiller, it's actually the importer, has to break down the liquor once it comes here... he doesn't care about the labels.", "start": 2291.341, "stop": 2300.9, "duration": 9.56, "cleanText": [["if", "the", "if", "the", "distiller", "it", "be", "actually", "the", "importer", "have", "to", "break", "down", "the", "liquor", "once", "it", "come", "here", "he", "do", "not", "care", "about", "the", "label"]]}, {"text": "It's the labor of doing this, instead of the way he normally does his business is just ship it to whichever state or ever local distributor he is going to.", "start": 2300.9, "stop": 2309.351, "duration": 8.45, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "the", "labor", "of", "do", "this", "instead", "of", "the", "way", "he", "normally", "do", "his", "business", "be", "just", "ship", "it", "to", "whichever", "state", "or", "ever", "local", "distributor", "he", "be", "go", "to"]]}, {"text": "And so I don't think it takes any leap of faith to understand why five of our prime source distributors said we are not going to do business with you any more.", "start": 2309.351, "stop": 2317.19, "duration": 7.84, "cleanText": [["and", "so", "i", "do", "not", "think", "it", "take", "any", "leap", "of", "faith", "to", "understand", "why", "five", "of", "our", "prime", "source", "distributor", "say", "we", "be", "not", "go", "to", "do", "business", "with", "you", "any", "more"]]}, {"text": "And one said well, we'll still do business but we are going to raise our prices.", "start": 2317.19, "stop": 2321.08, "duration": 3.89, "cleanText": [["and", "one", "say", "well", "we", "will", "still", "do", "business", "but", "we", "be", "go", "to", "raise", "our", "price"]]}, {"text": "And another curious aspect of the case is we will... the distributors and why they don't file their amicus brief, or why they are not here, we are going to still buy their liquor.", "start": 2321.08, "stop": 2329.076, "duration": 8, "cleanText": [["and", "another", "curious", "aspect", "of", "the", "case", "be", "we", "will", "the", "distributor", "and", "why", "they", "do", "not", "file", "their", "amicus", "brief", "or", "why", "they", "be", "not", "here", "we", "be", "go", "to", "still", "buy", "their", "liquor"]]}, {"text": "We are still going to be buying Johnnie Walker Black from Somerset Importers; we're just not going to be buying it directly from the shop.", "start": 2329.076, "stop": 2335.684, "duration": 6.61, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "still", "go", "to", "be", "buy", "johnnie", "walker", "black", "from", "somerset", "importer", "we", "be", "just", "not", "go", "to", "be", "buy", "it", "directly", "from", "the", "shop"]]}, {"text": "We're going to be buying it from Somerset Importers outlets in North Dakota.", "start": 2335.684, "stop": 2339.853, "duration": 4.17, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "go", "to", "be", "buy", "it", "from", "somerset", "importer", "outlet", "in", "north", "dakota"]]}, {"text": "So Somerset Importers says fine with us.", "start": 2339.853, "stop": 2341.931, "duration": 2.08, "cleanText": [["so", "somerset", "importer", "say", "fine", "with", "us"]]}, {"text": "And that is the problem, because under federal law the price differential from a distiller to a local importer is uniform.", "start": 2341.931, "stop": 2353.146, "duration": 11.22, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "the", "problem", "because", "under", "federal", "law", "the", "price", "differential", "from", "a", "distiller", "to", "a", "local", "importer", "be", "uniform"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you feel you may need amicus briefs to win this case?", "start": 2353.146, "stop": 2356.503, "duration": 3.36, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "feel", "you", "may", "need", "amicus", "brief", "to", "win", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Lazerwitz", "textObjs": [{"text": "At times I did, but I don't think... the government can stand on its own briefs and its own arguments.", "start": 2356.503, "stop": 2361.344, "duration": 4.84, "cleanText": [["at", "time", "i", "do", "but", "i", "do", "not", "think", "the", "government", "can", "stand", "on", "its", "own", "brief", "and", "its", "own", "argument"]]}, {"text": "Just one final point because the state does rely principally on the Twenty-first Amendment.", "start": 2361.344, "stop": 2367.076, "duration": 5.73, "cleanText": [["just", "one", "final", "point", "because", "the", "state", "do", "rely", "principally", "on", "the", "twenty", "first", "amendment"]]}, {"text": "Again, we have no quarrels with the idea that the state can take all sorts of measures to police trafficking of liquor within their borders.", "start": 2367.076, "stop": 2377.947, "duration": 10.87, "cleanText": [["again", "we", "have", "no", "quarrel", "with", "the", "idea", "that", "the", "state", "can", "take", "all", "sort", "of", "measure", "to", "police", "trafficking", "of", "liquor", "within", "their", "border"]]}, {"text": "But that is not this case because, even as Mr. Spaeth suggested, what they really concerned is what happens on the base.", "start": 2377.947, "stop": 2384.101, "duration": 6.15, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "be", "not", "this", "case", "because", "even", "as", "mr", "spaeth", "suggest", "what", "they", "really", "concern", "be", "what", "happen", "on", "the", "base"]]}, {"text": "And that is not something the Twenty-first Amendment gives them the authority to do.", "start": 2384.101, "stop": 2387.818, "duration": 3.72, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "not", "something", "the", "twenty", "first", "amendment", "give", "them", "the", "authority", "to", "do"]]}, {"text": "Off the base, that's a different matter.", "start": 2387.818, "stop": 2390.067, "duration": 2.25, "cleanText": [["off", "the", "base", "that", "be", "a", "different", "matter"]]}, {"text": "But on the base and the federal procurement is something that they can't do, and those are the Mississippi cases.", "start": 2390.067, "stop": 2395.377, "duration": 5.31, "cleanText": [["but", "on", "the", "base", "and", "the", "federal", "procurement", "be", "something", "that", "they", "can", "not", "do", "and", "those", "be", "the", "mississippi", "case"]]}, {"text": "So, no further questions.", "start": 2395.377, "stop": 2396.627, "duration": 1.25, "cleanText": [["so", "no", "further", "question"]]}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 2396.627, "stop": 2397.283, "duration": 0.66, "cleanText": [["thank", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, Mr. Lazerwitz.", "start": 2397.283, "stop": 2399.266, "duration": 1.98, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "mr", "lazerwitz"]]}, {"text": "General Spaeth, do you have rebuttal?", "start": 2399.266, "stop": 2401.624, "duration": 2.36, "cleanText": [["general", "spaeth", "do", "you", "have", "rebuttal"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think the Court understands the case, but I thought I would follow up on a couple of points that came up and perhaps the Court is also in doubt about the answer.", "start": 2401.624, "stop": 2411.871, "duration": 10.25, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "the", "court", "understand", "the", "case", "but", "i", "thought", "i", "would", "follow", "up", "on", "a", "couple", "of", "point", "that", "come", "up", "and", "perhaps", "the", "court", "be", "also", "in", "doubt", "about", "the", "answer"]]}, {"text": "The labels, which I showed to you before, are fairly effective because of their bright color in identifying someone who is accumulating large quantities of liquor for bootlegging, and they are subject, in that case, to--", "start": 2411.871, "stop": 2424.054, "duration": 12.18, "cleanText": [["the", "label", "which", "i", "show", "to", "you", "before", "be", "fairly", "effective", "because", "of", "their", "bright", "color", "in", "identify", "someone", "who", "be", "accumulate", "large", "quantity", "of", "liquor", "for", "bootlegging", "and", "they", "be", "subject", "in", "that", "case", "to"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "But you don't think it is going to add... be a deterrent effect to... I mean, somebody reads that label and says I should--", "start": 2424.054, "stop": 2433.051, "duration": 9, "cleanText": [["but", "you", "do", "not", "think", "it", "be", "go", "to", "add", "be", "a", "deterrent", "effect", "to", "i", "mean", "somebody", "read", "that", "label", "and", "say", "i", "should"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No.", "start": 2433.051, "stop": 2433.877, "duration": 0.83, "cleanText": [["no"]]}, {"text": "If they want to, if they are going to bootleg it off the base this isn't going to help.", "start": 2433.877, "stop": 2436.704, "duration": 2.83, "cleanText": [["if", "they", "want", "to", "if", "they", "be", "go", "to", "bootleg", "it", "off", "the", "base", "this", "be", "not", "go", "to", "help"]]}, {"text": "And it is not going to help in typical situations where someone takes one or two bottles off the base.", "start": 2436.704, "stop": 2441.405, "duration": 4.7, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "be", "not", "go", "to", "help", "in", "typical", "situation", "where", "someone", "take", "one", "or", "two", "bottle", "off", "the", "base"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, is it... what is the penalty for possessing liquor in North Dakota which has not been purchased through a wholesaler?", "start": 2441.405, "stop": 2448.544, "duration": 7.14, "cleanText": [["well", "be", "it", "what", "be", "the", "penalty", "for", "possess", "liquor", "in", "north", "dakota", "which", "have", "not", "be", "purchase", "through", "a", "wholesaler"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "It depends on... on how we find them.", "start": 2448.544, "stop": 2450.715, "duration": 2.17, "cleanText": [["it", "depend", "on", "on", "how", "we", "find", "them"]]}, {"text": "If we found someone with simply one or two bottles, we'd... we would not prosecute.", "start": 2450.715, "stop": 2455.212, "duration": 4.5, "cleanText": [["if", "we", "find", "someone", "with", "simply", "one", "or", "two", "bottle", "we", "would", "we", "would", "not", "prosecute"]]}, {"text": "My office--", "start": 2455.212, "stop": 2455.65, "duration": 0.44, "cleanText": [["my", "office"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, is there a violation?", "start": 2455.65, "stop": 2456.697, "duration": 1.05, "cleanText": [["well", "be", "there", "a", "violation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "--There could be.", "start": 2456.697, "stop": 2457.398, "duration": 0.7, "cleanText": [["there", "could", "be"]]}, {"text": "If we were to prove that that person took... intended then to redistribute it or resell it, that would be in violation of a host of state laws which impose criminal penalties as well as civil penalties.", "start": 2457.398, "stop": 2467.801, "duration": 10.4, "cleanText": [["if", "we", "we", "be", "to", "prove", "that", "that", "person", "take", "intend", "then", "to", "redistribute", "it", "or", "resell", "it", "that", "would", "be", "in", "violation", "of", "a", "host", "of", "state", "law", "which", "impose", "criminal", "penalty", "as", "well", "as", "civil", "penalty"]]}, {"text": "The criminal penalty is a Class A misdemeanor.", "start": 2467.801, "stop": 2469.988, "duration": 2.19, "cleanText": [["the", "criminal", "penalty", "be", "a", "class", "a", "misdemeanor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "So the penalties we are talking about is possession of liquor for resale?", "start": 2469.988, "stop": 2473.768, "duration": 3.78, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "penalty", "we", "be", "talk", "about", "be", "possession", "of", "liquor", "for", "resale"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct.", "start": 2473.768, "stop": 2474.502, "duration": 0.73, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "We would have to prove, of course, in the case of a single bottle, that they intended to do that, and undoubtedly we wouldn't prosecute in that case.", "start": 2474.502, "stop": 2479.984, "duration": 5.48, "cleanText": [["we", "would", "have", "to", "prove", "of", "course", "in", "the", "case", "of", "a", "single", "bottle", "that", "they", "intend", "to", "do", "that", "and", "undoubtedly", "we", "would", "not", "prosecute", "in", "that", "case"]]}, {"text": "But that is not what we are concerned about.", "start": 2479.984, "stop": 2481.685, "duration": 1.7, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "be", "not", "what", "we", "be", "concern", "about"]]}, {"text": "We are concerned more with the situation where its large quantities being moved off base, and we can identify them through the use of these labels.", "start": 2481.685, "stop": 2488.543, "duration": 6.86, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "concern", "more", "with", "the", "situation", "where", "its", "large", "quantity", "be", "move", "off", "base", "and", "we", "can", "identify", "them", "through", "the", "use", "of", "these", "label"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Isn't there some rule you're not supposed to be in possession of untaxed liquor in--", "start": 2488.543, "stop": 2492.042, "duration": 3.5, "cleanText": [["be", "not", "there", "some", "rule", "you", "be", "not", "suppose", "to", "be", "in", "possession", "of", "untaxed", "liquor", "in"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, we don't have a possession rule.", "start": 2492.042, "stop": 2494.368, "duration": 2.33, "cleanText": [["no", "we", "do", "not", "have", "a", "possession", "rule"]]}, {"text": "But we do have a rule, a law that prohibits possession with intent to resell.", "start": 2494.368, "stop": 2498.32, "duration": 3.95, "cleanText": [["but", "we", "do", "have", "a", "rule", "a", "law", "that", "prohibit", "possession", "with", "intent", "to", "resell"]]}, {"text": "And that is what we're, that is what our regulations are designed to do.", "start": 2498.32, "stop": 2502.194, "duration": 3.87, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "what", "we", "be", "that", "be", "what", "our", "regulation", "be", "design", "to", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "--General Spaeth, I had two questions.", "start": 2502.194, "stop": 2504.069, "duration": 1.88, "cleanText": [["general", "spaeth", "i", "have", "two", "question"]]}, {"text": "First, in view of the colloquy with your adversary, and you mentioned this, three cents a label, it is fairly clear, is it not, that if the wholesaler has to un, open up all these cartons and stick the labels on individual bottles, it is a substantial burden in labeling.", "start": 2504.069, "stop": 2519.841, "duration": 15.77, "cleanText": [["first", "in", "view", "of", "the", "colloquy", "with", "your", "adversary", "and", "you", "mention", "this", "three", "cent", "a", "label", "it", "be", "fairly", "clear", "be", "it", "not", "that", "if", "the", "wholesaler", "have", "to", "un", "open", "up", "all", "these", "carton", "and", "stick", "the", "label", "on", "individual", "bottle", "it", "be", "a", "substantial", "burden", "in", "label"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't know if it is substantial, but it is more than three cents a bottle.", "start": 2519.841, "stop": 2522.013, "duration": 2.17, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "know", "if", "it", "be", "substantial", "but", "it", "be", "more", "than", "three", "cent", "a", "bottle"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "It is a lot more if you have to open... I mean just opening a liquor case takes a little work, you know, and it's... and then getting each bottle--", "start": 2522.013, "stop": 2527.965, "duration": 5.95, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "a", "lot", "more", "if", "you", "have", "to", "open", "i", "mean", "just", "open", "a", "liquor", "case", "take", "a", "little", "work", "you", "know", "and", "it", "be", "and", "then", "get", "each", "bottle"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't know, I don't buy it by the case, but it could be more burdensome.", "start": 2527.965, "stop": 2531.775, "duration": 3.81, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "know", "i", "do", "not", "buy", "it", "by", "the", "case", "but", "it", "could", "be", "more", "burdensome"]]}, {"text": "[Laughter]", "start": 2531.775, "stop": 2532.463, "duration": 0.69, "cleanText": [["laughter"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "--And so that is what we are talking about, is that?", "start": 2532.463, "stop": 2534.273, "duration": 1.81, "cleanText": [["and", "so", "that", "be", "what", "we", "be", "talk", "about", "be", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 2534.273, "stop": 2534.461, "duration": 0.19, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}, {"text": "That is what we are talking about.", "start": 2534.461, "stop": 2534.976, "duration": 0.52, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "what", "we", "be", "talk", "about"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "And the second thing, is there... maybe you have answered it, I just wasn't entirely clear.", "start": 2534.976, "stop": 2539.397, "duration": 4.42, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "second", "thing", "be", "there", "maybe", "you", "have", "answer", "it", "i", "just", "be", "not", "entirely", "clear"]]}, {"text": "Does North Dakota require any kind of stamp on the bottle on which the tax is paid?", "start": 2539.397, "stop": 2544.411, "duration": 5.01, "cleanText": [["do", "north", "dakota", "require", "any", "kind", "of", "stamp", "on", "the", "bottle", "on", "which", "the", "tax", "be", "pay"]]}, {"text": "Is there anything... evidence it does?", "start": 2544.411, "stop": 2545.989, "duration": 1.58, "cleanText": [["be", "there", "anything", "evidence", "it", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, there is no labeling requirement.", "start": 2545.989, "stop": 2546.8, "duration": 0.81, "cleanText": [["no", "there", "be", "no", "labeling", "requirement"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Don't many states do that?", "start": 2546.8, "stop": 2547.91, "duration": 1.11, "cleanText": [["do", "not", "many", "state", "do", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "Some states do, but many states do not.", "start": 2547.91, "stop": 2549.674, "duration": 1.76, "cleanText": [["some", "state", "do", "but", "many", "state", "do", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yeah.", "start": 2549.674, "stop": 2550.158, "duration": 0.48, "cleanText": [["yeah"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "The last point I wanted to address, and then if there are any questions I will answer them, is the dispute we are having with the government about whether we could tax or not.", "start": 2550.158, "stop": 2558.404, "duration": 8.25, "cleanText": [["the", "last", "point", "i", "want", "to", "address", "and", "then", "if", "there", "be", "any", "question", "i", "will", "answer", "them", "be", "the", "dispute", "we", "be", "have", "with", "the", "government", "about", "whether", "we", "could", "tax", "or", "not"]]}, {"text": "And I know the Court doesn't like to listen to quotes, but if you look at your case United States v. Mississippi State Tax Commission, 421 U.S. at 613-614, the Court does say that nothing in the language of the Twenty-first Amendment leads to the extraordinary conclusion that the amendment abolished federal immunity with respect to sales, but it does, certainly does not say anything... excuse me, I am misreading it.", "start": 2558.404, "stop": 2580.692, "duration": 22.29, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "know", "the", "court", "do", "not", "like", "to", "listen", "to", "quote", "but", "if", "you", "look", "at", "your", "case", "united", "state", "v", "mississippi", "state", "tax", "commission", "us", "at", "the", "court", "do", "say", "that", "nothing", "in", "the", "language", "of", "the", "twenty", "first", "amendment", "lead", "to", "the", "extraordinary", "conclusion", "that", "the", "amendment", "abolish", "federal", "immunity", "with", "respect", "to", "sale", "but", "it", "do", "certainly", "do", "not", "say", "anything", "excuse", "me", "i", "be", "misread", "it"]]}, {"text": "There is the ability to tax, and I think, you know, that is clear based on a whole line of cases that this Court has declared.", "start": 2580.692, "stop": 2591.172, "duration": 10.48, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "the", "ability", "to", "tax", "and", "i", "think", "you", "know", "that", "be", "clear", "base", "on", "a", "whole", "line", "of", "case", "that", "this", "court", "have", "declare"]]}, {"text": "Are there any more questions?", "start": 2591.172, "stop": 2592.297, "duration": 1.13, "cleanText": [["be", "there", "any", "more", "question"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you General Spaeth.", "start": 2592.297, "stop": 2594.483, "duration": 2.19, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "general", "spaeth"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Nicholas Spaeth", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you.", "start": 2594.483, "stop": 2595.015, "duration": 0.53, "cleanText": [["thank", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "The case is submitted.", "start": 2595.015, "stop": 2595.827, "duration": 0.81, "cleanText": [["the", "case", "be", "submit"]]}]}]}], "decidedBy": "Rehnquist Court", "arguedOn": "Oct 31, 1989", "petitioner": "", "respondent": "", "docket": "88-926", "citation": "495US423(1990)", "justiaLink": "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/495/423", "lowerCourt": "United States Court of Appeals for the Eighth Circuit", "grantedOn": "", "decidedOn": "May 21, 1990"}